title: pineapple and cheese cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Add eggs and pineapple.
Bake in greased and floured pan, 9 x 9-inches or 8 x 12-inches.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix cranberries, apples and sugar and then place in buttered casserole.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over cranberries.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: christmas salad
directions: Cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Fold rest together.
Put in flat pan (oblong baking pan).
Decorate with red and green cherries to look like a red berry with 2 green leaves.
Place in freezer. Before serving, remove from freezer and thaw at least 45 minutes.

title: baked strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull strawberries; cut in half if very large.
Add sugar and cornstarch to berries; mix gently.
Turn into pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and dot with butter.
Cover with lattice crust or plain top crust with a few slashes cut in top.
Seal edges well and flute.
Bake at 425° on rack below center of oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 45 minutes longer or until filling has thickened.

title: kindergarten cookies (molasses)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add molasses.
Beat well.
Add egg; beat.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and spices; mix well. Roll in balls; dip in sugar.
Flatten balls with a tumbler.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: betty's chocolate cake
directions: Mix well and pour in greased and floured 9 x 9-inch cake pan and bake approximately 40 minutes or until toothpick test comes out clean.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Mix the milk, soups and dry soup mix in pan and heat thoroughly.
Spread Minute rice in bottom of dish.
Lay chicken pieces on rice.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Can remove foil to brown the last 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, onion soup, eggs and cracker crumbs together; roll into 1 inch balls. Place on cookie sheet and bake until brown at 375°. Mix tomato sauce, paste, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce in a saucepan. Stir until brown sugar dissolves, then simmer for 30 minutes. Pour over meatballs or dip meatballs in sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a greased pan for 45 minutes at 350°. Stir once or twice.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and margarine.
Add eggs. Beat smooth.
Pour over rhubarb in 9-inch pastry lined pan.
Top with pastry cut in fancy shapes.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° for about 30 minutes more.

title: classic strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg into a large bowl.
Cut in butter to resemble coarse meal.
Blend milk and egg yolks in a bowl with a fork.
Stir into flour mixture to make a soft dough.
Divide dough into six portions.
Form into balls.
Pat balls out on a greased baking sheet to 3-inch circles, moistening fingers with egg whites.
Brush cake with egg whites.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden.
Cut in half and top with strawberries and cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: herbed chicken legs
directions: Sprinkle legs with salt and pepper.
Turn them in oil to coat. Arrange skin side down in one layer in a baking dish.
Place in a 425° oven and bake 50 minutes.
Turn skin side up and sprinkle with mixture of bread crumbs, onion, garlic, parsley, thyme and rosemary.
Bake 1/2 hour longer.
Baste and cook another 10 minutes longer.
Pour around (not over) 1/3 cup dry white wine and bake 10 minutes longer.
Total cooking time is 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: marinated artichoke chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put
chicken breasts into a long baking casserole, skin side up.
Sprinkle garlic salt and soup mix on top of chicken.
Sprinkle soy sauce over all of chicken mixture. Evenly distribute
the
artichokes	with some of the oil.
Place mushrooms on
top.	Bake,
uncovered,
for	1
3/4 hours.
Serve with River Road Rice.

title: classic french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a screw-top jar or small bowl. Shake well or whip with wire whisk until ingredients are well blended and of a thick and creamy consistency.
Chill.
Refrigerate in tightly covered container.
Shake well before using.
Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in extract.
Add flour; mix well.
Shape level measuring tablespoons of dough into balls; roll in nuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Indent centers; fill with preserves. Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes, or until lightly browned. Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: almond punch
directions: Bring 1 quart of water to a boil.
Remove from heat, add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add 7 quarts of water.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serve hot or cold.
If you are using Sprite add it at the last minute.

title: hidden valley ranch pizzaettes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry on paper towels. Combine with cheeses, salad dressing, olives and red peppers. Grease mini muffin pans.
Press in wonton or egg roll wrappers. Brush with oil.
Bake 5 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from pans.
Place on baking sheets.
Fill with cheese dressing sausage mix.
Bake 5 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 5 dozen.
Delicious.

title: bolos de bacalhau(codfish cakes)
directions: Combine potatoes, codfish, pepper, parsley and eggs in a bowl. Form mixture into egg-shaped balls about 1 1/2-inches long; deep fry until brown.
Place on paper towel to absorb excess oil. Serve garnished with parsley sprigs, either cold or warm, from platter.
Yields about 20.

title: skinless chicken breasts
directions: Brown chicken breasts and simmer until done.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Very good eaten over rice or noodles.

title: chili sauce
directions: Put tomatoes, onion and peppers through a food chopper.
Mix all ingredients in a large pot.
Steep 2 1/2 hours.
Put in sterilized jars and seal tight.
Serve cold with meat.

title: chicken and peppers
directions: Prepare vegetables as for stir-fry.
Amounts can be determined according to number of servings desired.
Saute slowly in olive oil until done.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: stuffed zucchini hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut off ends of zucchini and carefully scoop out flesh with a long handled spoon.
In a small bowl, mix remaining ingredients and stuff zucchini with a pastry bag or small spoon, packing well. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill until serving time.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices and serve with picks.

title: dark chocolate cake with buttercream frosting
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: graham brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over hot water.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
In mixing bowl, combine melted chocolate, graham cracker crumbs, condensed milk, cinnamon, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Line an 8-inch square pan with waxed paper.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool in pan, then cut in squares.
Makes 16.

title: pecan cake squares
directions: Mix Bisquick and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix 2 1/2 cups of cheese and margarine into macaroni while hot.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Spray crock-pot with Pam. Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of cheese over top.
Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: cheezy chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in bottom of greased 9 x 13 pan. Mix soups and mayonnaise. Stir well. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle shredded cheese over all. Sprinkle stuffing crumbs over all. Drizzle melted butter over top. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350 degrees. Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain off juice of Veg-All.
Layer in casserole dish the Veg-All, cheese and crackers.
Pour melted butter over all. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in one cup warm water in large mixing bowl.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook as biscuits in muffin pan.
Put in cold oven and turn to 450° until lightly browned.

title: spanish style rice
directions: Combine tomato sauce, water, onion, pepper, oleo, salt, mustard and pepper in saucepan. Cover and bring to a full boil. Stir in rice. Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Stir with fork.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place peeled and sliced vegetables in crock-pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put cooked ground beef on top of vegetables. Mix soup and water together and place on top of beef.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours (high 3 to 4 hours), stirring occasionally.

title: smores cheesecake
directions: Crush 14 crackers and add butter and 1/4 c. sugar.
Mix well, press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chop other 4 graham crackers, reserve. Mix cream cheese and remaining 1 cup sugars and vanilla with mixer. Add eggs; mix until blended.
Stir in 1/2 of candy, pour into crust.
Sprinkle with remaining candy, marshmallows and graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until center is almost set. Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Cut into bars.

title: deb's chicken pie
directions: Mix
chicken,
mushroom
soup,	vegetables
and chicken broth and put in baking dish.
Stir together buttermilk, flour and margarine.	Pour over pie and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and add Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole crackers; layer 1/2 pudding, then crackers, then pudding, then crackers.
Melt 1 tub chocolate icing for 60 seconds in microwave.
Pour this over the crackers.

title: child cold shake
directions: Fill cup with ice cream.
Add milk and syrup.
Stir all together until slushy.
Now you have a child cold shake.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given, folding in eggs last. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: dill sauce
directions: Add dill to white sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Season with salt.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat 5 minutes. Pour into two 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Slice and serve with sweetened cheese spread.

title: cranberry relish mold
directions: Combine gelatin and sugar; dissolve in hot water.
Add cold water, lemon juice and pineapple syrup.
Chill until mixture begins to set.
Add pineapple and remaining ingredients; turn into 2-quart mold.
Yields 12 servings.

title: fried chicken
directions: Combine flour and seasonings.
Shake chicken in seasonings; fry in medium heat.
Brown well.
Transfer to a Dutch oven.
Add water and onion.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: taco cheesecake
directions: Stir together the crushed tortilla chips and melted margarine. Press in bottom of 8 inch spring form pan. Bake 325° for 10 minutes. Cool. Cook beef in large skillet over medium heat and drain. Stir in taco seasoning mix (reserve 1 teaspoon) and water. Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes. Beat cream cheese at medium speed till fluffy and add eggs and 1 teaspoon taco seasoning. Add cheddar cheese and blend. Spread over crust and up i inch on sides. Spoon in the meat mixture and spread the cream cheese mixture around the sides of the pan over the beef mixture forming a border. Combine the sour cream and flour and spread over the top of meat mixture. Bake 325° for 25 minutes, cool 10 minutes and remove sides of pan. Serve warm with toppings of chopped lettuce, green pepper and tomatoes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water.
Drain; rinse.
Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add soup, milk and poultry seasoning; heat.
Beat cheeses together.
Stir in olives and parsley.

title: taco salad(salad or main dish)
directions: Brown and cool hamburger meat and onion.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Top with grated cheese; serve with chips and picante sauce.

title: gold nugget macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In a large pan, saute onion in the butter.
Add corn, salt and pepper. Heat through.
Stir in cheese and macaroni.
Pour into dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: pepper onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: layered ranch dip
directions: Combine ranch dip mix and sour cream. Spread in a shallow dish. Layer other ingredients in the order listed. Serve with toasted corn chips.

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring sugar, water and syrup to boil.
Add peanuts and food coloring; boil until it gets to hard ball on candy thermometer, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Add oleo and salt; remove from heat. Beat until thick; pour into buttered pan or make patties.

title: linguini with chicken and peanut sauce
directions: Cut chicken into bite sized pieces; set aside.

title: jean blanc's hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until blended.
Add milk and bring to a boil stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Put over ice cream or pound cake, etc.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion, tomato sauce and green peppers.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add this to the cooked noodles, mushrooms and cheese loaf.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: "never fail" brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Brown together beef, onion and celery.
Add chestnuts, mushrooms, rice, pepper and soy sauce to mixture.
Add enough water to the saved liquids from chestnuts and mushrooms to make 2 cups.
Add to beef mixture.
Stir just to mix.
Put in covered casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except pie crust.
When well mixed, pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peach pickles
directions: Cook sugar, vinegar and spices for 20 minutes.
Drop in peaches a few at a time and cook until tender.
Put in hot sterilized jars, adding syrup to within 1/2-inch of top.
Seal. Yields 6 pints.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add whole eggs one at a time.
Sprinkle meal over mixture and add vinegar and vanilla. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven 40 minutes or until set.

title: meat loaf
directions: Chop onion into small pieces.
Throughly mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Form into a loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
For best results, bake loaf on a broiler pan.
Enjoy!

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening.
Add sugar and egg yolks.
Mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in coconut and chopped pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
This will make 4 (8-inch) layers or 3 (9-inch) layers.
Bake at 350°.
Grease pans well and dust with flour. Cool before icing with cream cheese frosting.

title: pickled red beets and eggs
directions: Drain juice of beets and add enough water to liquid to make 1 cup.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Bring juice to a boil. Pour hot juice over beets and hard-boiled eggs and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Ease rolled out crust into 9-inch pie plate.
In a large bowl, gently toss blueberries, lemon peel, cinnamon, 1/2 cup sugar and remaining flour.
Spoon blueberry mixture into crust.
Cut margarine or butter into small pieces; sprinkle on top of blueberry mixture.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Moisten edge of crust with water; place top crust over filling.
Trim dough edge, leaving 1-inch overhang.
Fold overhang under; make fluted edge. With a sharp knife, cut 4-inch "X" in center of top crust.
Fold back points of "X" to make a square opening in the center of the pie.
Sprinkle top of pie with remaining 2 teaspoons sugar.
Bake 40 minutes or until filling begins to bubble and crust is golden. If crust browns too quickly, cover edge loosely with foil.
Cool pie on rack.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Brown chicken breasts.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken breasts.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: chicken and cheese casserole
directions: Heat oven 350.
In glass 9x13 inch baking dish place chicken pieces.
Place single layer cheese on top of chicken.
Mix soup and milk and pour over cheese layer.
Cover with stuffing mixture and foil.
Bake 350 for 1 hour.
Do not peek.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Add Jell-O and fruit.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
Add flour, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Form into small balls, then flatten slightly with a fork.
Can put colored sugar on.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen small cookies that taste like shortbread.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and salt together.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Mix well after each and pour into floured surface.
Work in more flour in dough until you can pick up without sticking to hands.
Place in large bowl and place in refrigerator over night.
Next morning knead dough and roll out. Bake at 400 degrees.

title: bing cherry mold
directions: Heat 1 cup cherry juice and Port.
Pour remaining juice over plain
gelatin.
Put
both gelatins together and dissolve in the hot cherry juice.
Stir and mix together.
Add cherries stuffed with pecan halves.	Put in mold.
Serves 6.

title: beef stew
directions: Put ingredients in crock-pot on low.
Cook all day (everything at once).
Great for working wives!!

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour, sifted with soda.
Add sour cream, vanilla and lemon juice.
Mix chopped nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Pour half of batter into well-greased spring-form pan; sprinkle 3/4 of nut mixture over batter, then add rest of batter.
Sprinkle remaining nut mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter lovers dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl; beat at low speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit (apple slices, banana chunks and grapes).

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Use a hand mixer and beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in 2 cups of Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: baked corn
directions: Add beaten egg whites last.
Bake in buttered casserole in pan of water and bake until brown.

title: fold-over apple raisin pie
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups flour and salt in a medium bowl.
Cut in butter and shortening with a pastry blender until coarse crumbs form.
Sprinkle with water and shape into ball.
Wrap pastry in waxed paper.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: golden onion pork chops
directions: Mix soup mix and bread crumbs together.
Dip pork chops into beaten egg, then roll into onion/bread crumb mixture.
Place pork chops in a casserole dish and put pats of butter all around.
Cover and let cook for about 35 minutes.
Uncover and turn pork chops over and let cook, uncovered, for another 25 minutes or until golden brown or crispy.
Delicious!!!!

title: sunday pot roast
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add beef; brown on all sides.
Remove roast and place on a plate.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in Dutch oven until tender.
Add tomato sauce and water; stir to blend.
Return beef to pot.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Reduce to low heat; cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cover and continue cooking 30 minutes or until tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese souffle sandwiches(brunch)
directions: Make 6 sandwiches, each with 1 slice bread, 1 slice cheese, meat and 1 slice bread.
Place sandwiches in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°
about 35 minutes.

title: orange spritz cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Mix shortening, sugars, orange peel, juice, vanilla and egg.
Beat until light and fluffy. Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.

title: pan baked potato halves
directions: In small glass	bowl, melt oleo on High (max power) for 45 seconds.
In separate bowl, mix cheese and seasonings.
Cut washed potatoes
in
half,
lengthwise.
Dip cut side in oleo, then in cheese mixture.
Place potato, cut side up, in 2 quart baking dish.
Cook on High (max power) for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Let
stand
minutes.
Sprinkle cut side with paprika and serve hot.

title: half pound cake
directions: Cream together; add 1 egg at a time.
Add milk, alternating with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: no sugar apple pie(serves 8)
directions: This is a recipe for those who have to limit their sugar.
It is a little tart, but with Cool Whip or no sugar frozen dessert on top, it tastes good to those of us who can't tolerate much sugar.

title: beef bits
directions: In a large roasting pan, place seasoned beef bits and soups. After beef bits have cooked awhile add vinegar and cook in an uncovered pan until tender, stirring frequently.

title: mexi-dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chips.
Chill.

title: onion rings
directions: Beat egg; add remaining ingredients in order.
Beat until smooth.
Coat onion rings well with batter.
Deep-fry until brown.

title: five bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon and onions; stir in everything but beans.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes.
Pour over beans in crock-pot. Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine white sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Divide each biscuit into 3 pieces and roll each in sugar-cinnamon mixture. Place in tube pan and sprinkle with pecans.
Repeat layers.
Melt margarine, 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Bring to boil and pour all over balls.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or less.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french fry casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add salt, pepper, soup and soup can of milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover with French fries.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake until hot and French fries are cooked through at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: french meat pie
directions: In a skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Remove and set aside.
Brown beef and pork together; drain.
Combine onion, meat, potatoes and seasonings.
Line pie plate with pastry; fill with meat mixture.
Top with other crust. Brush with egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: grandma's light bread
directions: Cook the potatoes and mash.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add yeast water to the mashed potatoes along with salt and sugar.
Mix well; place in a crock and leave it on a warm hearth to rise.
When mixture has risen almost to the top of crock, begin to add flour until you have a firm dough.
Let rise until double in size.
Then knead real good before shaping into loaves.
Let rise again, then bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, or until broomstraw stuck in comes out free of dough.
Slice and spread with butter.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thin slices but not all the way through; use handle of spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Place potatoes in a baking dish and fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt, butter and herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes, until potatoes are tender and cheeses have melted.

title: potato latkes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes onto paper towels.
Squeeze out excess water and place potatoes in a mixing bowl.
Peel and grate onion into potatoes.
Add eggs and mix.
Then mix in flour and salt. Heat oil in a skillet.
Drop tablespoonfuls of batter into skillet. Fry on both sides until crisp and brown.
Drain on paper towels. Serve warm with applesauce.
Serving:
3 latkes.

title: cucumber sandwich filling
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and let soak until moisture builds up.
Squeeze dry (don't rinse).
Mix all ingredients. Chill overnight or at least 4 hours.
Soften to spread on bread. I use rye bread.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender; combine thoroughly.
Pour into a 9-inch glass pie dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until set.

title: big-batch beef sauce
directions: In a Dutch oven over medium heat, cook beef, onions, celery and garlic until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender. Drain. Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Cool. Transfer to freezer bags or containers, about 2 cups in each bag. May be frozen for 3 months. Yields about 15 cups total.

title: grandmother's cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries, apples and oranges through food chopper.
Add sugar and Jell-O dissolved in boiling water.
(If desired, put oranges through blender to avoid pieces of peeling.)

title: marshmallow bunnies
directions: Line 15 x 10-inch pan with brown paper.
Soften packages of gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
In 2-quart saucepan, mix 1 cup sugar, 1 cup syrup and 1/3 cup water.
Cook, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Cook, without stirring, to soft ball stage (240°). Stir in gelatin and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool 10 minutes.
Slowly add beaten egg white to syrup mixture, beating on high speed to make soft peaks.
Spread candy into pan; let stand uncovered, overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add oil, white sugar and brown sugar. Sift together soda, cinnamon, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Will be fairly firm. Fold in zucchini, vanilla and nuts.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Bring all ingredients slowly to boiling point.
Simmer 3 hours.
Add 3/4 cup creamery butter.
Pour into jars and seal, or put into containers and freeze.

title: large strawberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries, bananas and pineapple.
Mix well and congeal.
Soften cream cheese and add vanilla and powdered sugar.
Slowly add to Dream Whip.
Spread over congealed salad and sprinkle nuts on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken juice.
Mix all ingredients except cheese; top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°, uncovered.
Serve with corn chips.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavorings.
Combine flour and soda; add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes and cool thoroughly.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter bread and tear in bite size. Put bread in buttered 9 x 13 dish. Mix all ingredients. Pour over bread. Let sit in refrigerator 1 hour. Drop sugar, butter and cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: italian delight
directions: Cook meat, onion and green pepper.
Add other ingredients, except cheese and macaroni.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Combine with cheese and macaroni; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes about a gallon.

title: daisy's sweet rice
directions: Mix rice, water, milk, butter and salt.
Bring to a boil, turn heat on low for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Stir into rice mixture slowly.
Add vanilla. Raisins may be added if desired.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and all other ingredients in bowl
together.
Then pour in ice cream bucket.
Finish up to line with whole or 2 percent milk.

title: garlic green beans
directions: In nonstick skillet over medium heat, combine beans, olive oil and garlic. Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Remove cover, stir and cook 3 minutes longer or until liquid evaporates. Season to taste and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Makes 4 servings.

title: crazy biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients, roll out dough and cut with cutter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Add grated cheese, cream of mushroom soup and mayonnaise, then add chopped onion and pimento. Top with crushed Ritz crackers and top crackers with melted butter.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add beans and heat for 10 minutes and then chill.
Tear lettuce and add tomatoes cut into bite size and onion.
Just before serving, add French dressing to taste, cheese and taco chips.

title: chicken bites
directions: Cover 2 baking sheets with foil.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Mix cracker crumbs, cheese, walnuts, seasoned salt, thyme, basil and pepper.
Heat oven to 400°. Dip chicken pieces into melted butter, then into crumb mixture.
Place chicken pieces about 1/2-inch apart on baking sheets. Bake, uncovered, until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix pot pie mixture and pour into the greased casserole dish. Bake at
350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Put ketchup in a big bowl; add rest of ingredients to your taste.
Take funnel and put it in ketchup bottle you just emptied. Keep in refrigerator.
Use as needed.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet and reduce heat under bacon grease.
Chop 1 large onion and simmer in bacon grease until translucent, not brown.
Add cooked spaghetti, salt, pepper and sugar.
Toss until spaghetti is covered.
Add tomato sauce and heat until hot.
Add crumbled bacon strips and serve.

title: plantation pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually, then add syrup and evaporated milk.
In another bowl add salt to eggs and beat until light.
Stir well into first mixture; add vanilla and pecans.
Use 1 cup nuts for halves or 1 1/2 cups if broken into pieces.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer.

title: easy cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lisa's chicken
directions: Place chicken in a single layer in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients, except noodles or rice, and pour over chicken. Marinate at least 8 hours, refrigerated.
Bake in pan at 350° for 1 hour, turning twice.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: easy toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line the bottom of a well-greased 15 1/4 x 10 1/4 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with crackers.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Combine syrup and sugar in pan and bring to a full boil; remove immediately from heat.
Mix in peanut butter and cereal. Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in a double boiler.
Spread as icing over the first mixture.
Cool and cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.

title: mini meat loaves(or meat balls)
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and 1/8 teaspoon each pepper, sage and thyme.
Shape firmly into small (about 6) mini meat loaves.
In skillet, brown loaves in shortening.
Drain fat.
Mix together remaining ingredients (soup, seasonings and water) and set aside.
Cover meat loaves and cook low heat 20 minutes.
Add soup mixture.
Cover again and cook low until done.
Stir occasionally. Serve with parsleyed potatoes and broccoli.

title: grilled ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Layer bread with American cheese, ham, tomato, onion, oregano, Cheddar cheese and ham.
Top with second bread slice.
Spread margarine on bread.
Grill in medium hot frying pan, lightly oiled.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt butter.
Mix butter and all else but chips.
Press into miniature muffin tins lined with fluted papers.
Melt chocolate chips and spoon on top of peanut butter mixture.
Chill or place in cookie tins and store in cool place.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: Cook asparagus in salted water until tender; drain.
Cool and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Place Swiss cheese in bottom of raw pie crust.
Arrange asparagus on top of cheese.
Blend eggs, half and half, salt and pepper.
Pour slowly over asparagus and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Test with knife for doneness. Cool 5 to 7 minutes before cutting.

title: reese's balls
directions: In medium bowl, combine powdered sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Heat 1/2 cup butter and 1/2 cup peanut butter until melted.
Stir into crumb mixture.
Make into balls and refrigerate.
Chill
until hard.
Melt 3 squares and 1 tablespoon butter.
Roll balls in chocolate with toothpicks.
Place on wax paper until hard.
Yield: 36 small balls.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli flowerettes, onion and crumbled crisp bacon. Make dressing with mayonnaise, sugar and cider vinegar.
Cover broccoli with dressing.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Tastes even better the next day!

title: rolls(makes 60 to 70)
directions: Mix together milk, sugar and shortening; bring to boil.
Cool to lukewarm; add well beaten eggs, salt, yeast and 8 cups flour; stir until smooth.
Let rise 2 hours.
Add 1 cup flour sifted with soda and baking powder.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Roll out 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Beat eggs until lemon color.
Add sugar and oleo.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts. Spread thin on a large cookie pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: aunt bills brown candy
directions: Pour 1 pint sugar in heavy iron skillet and place over low heat.
Begin stirring with a wooden spoon and keep sugar moving so it will not scorch.
It will take almost a half hour to completely melt this sugar and at no time let it smoke or cook so fast that it turns dark, it should be about the color of light brown sugar.

title: beef 'n tater bake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Pat meat into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; drain excess fat.
Combine 3 cups hot mashed potatoes and 3/4 cup shredded cheese and spread over meat.
Top with 1/4 cup shredded cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Boil in salted water until tender, drain and mash.
Mix in oleo, egg, milk and pepper to taste.
Pour into baking dish, cover with cracker crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed.
If using canned vegetables, drain cans.
Saute celery and onions in 2 tablespoons oleo. Combine vegetables, celery, onions, mayonnaise and cheese.
Put all into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: ellie learn's saltine buckle
directions: Cover large cookie sheet with foil up the sides.
Place saltines side by side on cookie sheet, being sure no space is left (cut crackers to fit).
Melt butter; add sugar.
Boil 2 minutes. Pour over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Immediately when taking from the oven, sprinkle with both kinds of chips.
As they melt, spread to cover crackers.
(Optional:
Sprinkle with nuts or coconut.)
Allow to cool, then place in refrigerator for 20 to 30 minutes.
Break or cut apart as you choose.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour 1/2 mixture in pan. Add grated cheese (sprinkle on).
Add rest of batter.
Bake at 400° in preheated oven for 45 minutes, or until brown.

title: jalapeno hush puppies
directions: Heat 2 or 3 inches Crisco in deep fryer or deep saucepan. Combine cornmeal, flour, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Stir in buttermilk, egg and onion; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons, a few at a time, into shortening.
Fry 2 minutes or until golden brown. Turn as needed for even browning.
Remove with slotted metal spoon.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour into baking dish and add pie filling.
Bake 30 minutes at 375° or until done.

title: turkey
directions: Take
a
turkey and clean it.
Remove giblets and neck. Put peanut oil all over the turkey, also inside.
Now salt and pepper inside and out.
I put my turkey in a roasting pan with cover on and bake at 325° for 20 minutes per pound of turkey, if it
is stuffed.
Roast
at
for 10 to 15 minutes per pound of turkey, if not stuffed.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large bowl, add all ingredients and shake.
Empty into roasting pan.
Bake for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add milk, bananas, vanilla and nuts.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add to cream mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken curry
directions: In a large frying pan saute onions in oil.
Mix together on a plate curry powder, salt, cumin, coriander and turmeric.
Coat chicken in dry mixture and fry in pan with onions until lightly browned and firm to touch.
Grind in blender until liquid, green chilies, ginger root, garlic and water.
Add this mixture and stir to blend with chicken. Simmer chicken until tender adding water as necessary to keep a cup or more of sauce on chicken.
Serve with plain cooked rice and condiments.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in small bowl; set aside.
Trim off large leaves of broccoli and remove tough ends.
Cut stalks into 1/4-inch slices.
Cut remaining broccoli into flowerets. Place in large salad bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour dressing over top; toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill one hour. Makes 8 to 10 servings.
I make it the day before.

title: grandma meda's sugar icebox cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Make into 2 rectangles of dough. Roll into waxed paper.
Chill overnight. Slice very thin (1/4-inch or less).
Bake in a 350° oven until golden on the edges.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet.
These freeze well.

title: macaroni and beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, water and soup mix.
Add macaroni.
Pour into casserole. Top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dreamy raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; set aside to cool.
Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise; blend well.
Stir into gelatin along with all remaining ingredients, except whipped topping.
Fold in whipped topping.,
Spoon into an 8-inch square pan; refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yield: 9 servings.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Mix well and bake at 250° for 5 hours in covered dish.
Do not peek!

title: pineapple sour cream cake
directions: Combine pineapple with baking soda in a small bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
In a large bowl combine cake mix and all remaining ingredients.
Add pineapple mixture.
Blend well.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch fluted (Bundt) pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Finish cooling on rack.
Frost with icing.

title: ham-fettuccine bake
directions: In skillet, lightly brown onions in butter.
Stir in soup, milk and 3/4 cup cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Blend sauce with ham and fettuccine.
Add cooked peas and chopped artichoke hearts.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
(I season mostly with black pepper; ham tends to have enough salt.)

title: orange drink
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth. Drink Up!

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: In casserole, combine peas, tomato sauce, mustard, bell pepper, salt, black pepper and hot red pepper. Add sliced onions to top. Spread with catsup and then top with sausage.
Bake at 350° until sausage is brown.

title: congealed salad *
directions: Mix lime Jell-O, 1 3/4 cups water and pineapple; let congeal. Mix lemon Jell-O, 2 cups water, cream cheese and nuts.
Pour over congealed lime Jell-O.
Mix red Jell-O and 2 cups of water.
Pour over lemon Jell-O.

title: 12-day pickles
directions: Days 1 - 7:
Slice 2 gallons cucumbers.
Soak in 1 gallon cold water and 1 pint salt for 7 days.

title: sparkling pineapple drink
directions: Fill each of 6 glasses 2/3 full of pineapple juice.
Add club soda or seltzer and ice cubes.
Garnish with strawberries, lime slices or pineapple chunks.

title: bacon cheddar quiche
directions: Cook bacon.
Mix eggs and milk together.
Add cheese, onion and bacon.
Flute pie crust and line with a layer of foil.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes until pie crust is done.
Reduce oven to 325°. Pour egg mixture into hot pie crust.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Great with salad.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda.
Combine margarine, sugar, pudding mix and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add in the flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: cherry pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and put in bottom of each pie crust. Sprinkle pecans on top of mixture. Next layer, Cool Whip. Finish with 1/2 can of pie filling into middle of each pie. Chill.

title: company chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in oleo and take out of pan. Add onion and flour.
Add mushrooms and wine to flour
mixture.
Pour
over chicken breasts.
Bake at 325° for 1 3/4 hours.
Serves 8.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Use an oblong cake pan or baking dish.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and milk. Beat by hand until smooth.
Pour into the buttered baking dish; do not stir!
Spoon in 1 can of fruit pie filling.
Take knife and swirl one time.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: microwave caramels
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, light corn syrup, milk and salt in 2-quart bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Stir twice during cooking.
Remove plastic wrap and continue cooking for 16 to 18 minutes at 70% or Medium-high.
Stir in vanilla and pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish. Cool and cut into pieces.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Using nonstick skillet, cook ground beef while breaking with a fork.
Sprinkle beef with onion and garlic powder.
Add tomatoes, paste, oregano and basil.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: brochettes
directions: Crush garlic cloves and saute briefly in olive oil.
Toast the bread pieces in a toaster oven or broiler.
Brush the bread with the garlic oil.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Top with tomato and basil.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Add pepper if desired.

title: classic lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and eggs. Brown beef.
Pour off fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Layer in long baking dish in the following order: spaghetti sauce mixture, noodles and cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook the ground beef until done and season.
Place ground beef in pan.
Add cheese and French-cut beans, then add 2 cans of cream of mushroom.
Spread smooth and add potato tots until covered completely.
Put in oven at 375° until potato tots are golden brown.

title: pepsi salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil; add jellos until dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir well.
Add cherries and Diet Pepsi.
Pour into an 8-inch dish and refrigerate until jelled.
Makes 8 servings. Each serving equals 1 fruit plus 8 calories.

title: easy beer bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add beer in thirds.
Batter will foam and make stiff dough.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Smooth over top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Upon removing from oven, smear top with butter or margarine (about 1/8 pound).
Cool on rack.
Raisins, nuts and cinnamon are optional.

title: sticky buns
directions: In bottom of large baking pan, mix sugar, margarine, pudding and nuts.
Place rolls on top in rows of 8.
Put in a cold oven overnight.
Next morning, turn oven on to 325° for 20 minutes. Invert onto plate to serve.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Line pie shells with half of cheese.
Top with sausage.
Pour mixed ingredients over sausage.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs one at a time beating well after each.
Add cake flour one cup at at time.
Mix well. Add flavoring.
Bake in a 10 inch tube pan, greased and floured. Start in a cold oven at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: pistachio bundt cake
directions: Beat oil, water and milk at medium speed until mixed. Add eggs and beat 2 minutes. Add pudding mix and cake mix (will be rather stiff). Add flavoring. Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 55 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: two way minestrone
directions: Cut fish or poultry into 1-inch pieces.
In a large saucepan, stir in broth, beans, vegetables, onion, pasta and spices.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered for 10 minutes.
Stir in undrained tomatoes.
Add fish or poultry.
Return to boiling, reduce heat.
Simmer covered.
For fish, allow 2 to 3 minutes.
For poultry, allow 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt or tube pan.
Have eggs and sour cream at room temperature.
Grate German chocolate.
Combine all ingredients, except the chocolate; mix well.
Fold in grated chocolate and chips.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: apricot-pineapple fluff
directions: Bring pineapple to a full boil in saucepan. Add Jell-O. Add water and mix well.
Put into large bowl and chill until slightly thickened. Add Cool Whip and beat until fluffy. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until set.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream flour and butter.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar. Sprinkle 1/2 of this mixture on cooled crust.
Prepare vanilla instant pudding.
Pour the prepared pudding on top of the peanut butter and powdered sugar mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding layer.
Top with the remaining crumbly mixture.
Cool. Enjoy!

title: green beans parmesan
directions: Melt butter in pan. Add shallots and cook until golden. In another pan, bring water to a boil. Add beans and cook 10 to 12 minutes. Drain beans. Stir in shallots, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese. Serves 8.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
(Batter will be thin.)
Bake in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Put ingredients in a crock-pot and turn on low.
Pour over tortilla chips or use as a dip.

title: apple baked pork chops
directions: Trim all fat from chops.
Place chops in baking dish.
Cut apples in half and remove cores.
Place each half apple on a pork chop.
Spread butter or margarine on each apple and sprinkle each with 1 teaspoon brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: susie's munchies
directions: Mix thoroughly the Ranch, dill, garlic powder and oil into the crackers.
Bake at 150° for 2 hours.
Stir frequently.
Cool. Enjoy!

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and can be used as a dip for fresh vegetables.
Can also be used for a rye bread dip by hollowing out a round rye bread and filling it with dip.

title: foolproof chocolate fudge
directions: Over low heat, melt chips, milk and salt in heavy saucepot. Do not boil.
Remove from heat and stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread in wax paper-lined 8 or 9-inch square pan and let set for 2 hours until firm, then cut into squares.
Good eating!

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add sour cream.
Mix in Cool Whip. Layer cookies with bananas and pudding.

title: hot broccoli-cauliflower vegetable
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower following directions on packages until they are just about done, not quite.
Add onions and carrots.
Arrange vegetables in casserole dish.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Place onions and potatoes in buttered baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over potatoes and onions.
Place chips of butter on top (about 3 tablespoons).
Cover and bake for about 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover and let brown slightly.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend for about 1 minute.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: banana daffodil
directions: Heat water and sugar in large saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients except ginger ale and freeze.
Thaw 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving.
In blender, mix 1 part Daffodil to 1 part ginger ale.
May be served as a frozen slush or liquid over ice.

title: snack mix
directions: Heat oven to slow (300°).
Place first five ingredients in shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan; cook over low heat until butter melts, stirring occasionally.
Pour butter mixture over cereal-nut combination, stirring until coated.
Toast in preheated oven about 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Smooth cream cheese in glass pie plate. Pour salsa over cream cheese. Sprinkle cheese over salsa. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Measure flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and sugar; sift flour and add.
Combine ingredients in one bowl; stir mixture to blend.
Pour into a greased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool at least 10 minutes.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Blend shortening and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix and add sour cream; mix separately the nuts, cinnamon and sugar.
Mix cranberry sauce up a bit.
Use a tube or Bundt pan.
Put 1/2 of batter in greased pan; put in 1/2 of the nut mix and 1/2 of cranberry sauce.
Put in remaining ingredients, nut mix and spread cranberry sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hurricane gloria
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice vegetables and put in large casserole dish.
Add ground meat and mix well.
Add water and cook for 1/2 hour.
Stir and add more water if needed.
Cook for 1/2 hour more.

title: enchiladas casserole
directions: Layer each one at a time.

title: pear harlequin
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight, except cherries. Next day cook until thick and add chopped cherries.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook fish and scallops in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Place in bowl.
Add sherry; let sit for 15 minutes.
Add scallops, fish and cream of shrimp soup to buttered casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bahamian fish soup
directions: Cut up salt pork into tiny pieces.
Use Wesson oil in small skillet to brown salt pork.
Add salt pork and drippings to 2 quarts boiling water in soup pot.
Chop up onions and celery and add to pot.
Season with butter or margarine, bay leaves, basil, oregano, cumin powder and crushed red pepper to make spicy.
Let boil until cooked.
Cut fish filet into small chunks.
Add fish to pot and let boil 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve over steamed rice. Serves 6 to 8 guests.

title: chicken curry, southern
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, brown chicken.
Remove chicken from skillet.
In drippings in skillet, cook garlic, onions, celery, green pepper, curry powder and salt until vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes and their liquid; add chicken pieces and heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 40 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Prepare rice and add raisins.

title: tropical fruit salad
directions: Cut fruit into serving pieces and mix together.
Mix salad dressing made from yogurt, sugar, salt and orange juice.
Pour dressing over salad and mix thoroughly.
Cover fruit salad and place in refrigerator.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with fresh grated coconut just prior to serving.
Serves 4.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Chop fine the pepper and onion.
Mix meal, eggs and oil.
Add buttermilk, corn, cheese, pepper and onion.
Mix well.
Bake in iron skillet at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beef onion casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: stuffed sweet pepper
directions: Cut peppers in half (take out seeds).
Cook 3 minutes in water; drain well.
Brown beef, onion and oil; add tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Put peppers in baking dish and fill with hamburger mixture until covered.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Break pasta in half before cooking.
Mix with other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: mammy's macaroni and cheese
directions: Use 2 to 3 quart casserole dish.
Layer with thin layer of macaroni, cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Continue to layer until full (about 3 layers).
Mix together milk and eggs.
Pour over macaroni mixture, about 1/4-inch from top.
Melt butter and crumble in crackers mix.
Spread over top and cook in 425° oven approximately 1/2 hour or until milk is no longer runny and crackers browned.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Heat skillet; form sausage into small balls (may make large balls for a main dish meat). Brown in skillet; drain meatballs on paper towels.
Drain fat from skillet and add catsup, brown sugar, soy sauce, lemon juice and the reserved pineapple juice.
Add meatballs.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add pineapple tidbits and simmer 10 minutes. Serve meatballs from a chafing dish, or as a main dish with rice. Makes about 50 cocktail meatballs.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Add all ingredients except cinnamon and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm topped with whipped cream.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray.
Press out package of cookie dough on cookie sheet.
Bake cookie until golden brown at temperature suggested on the roll of dough.
Blend together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread this mixture on the cookie after it cools.
Then top with your choice of garnish fruits.
Refrigerate until served.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the water and dry pectin and whisk until the pectin is mostly dissolved.
You can get dry pectin in the canning section of the grocery store.
Add the remaining ingredients, except for the Romano cheese, and place the pan over medium heat.
Stir often until the mixture begins to boil, then remove the pan from the heat.
Cool for about 10 minutes.
Stir in the Romano cheese in to the thickened mixture.
Allow the mixture to cool thoroughly, then pour it into a sealed container and chill for at least 2 hours.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine for a few minutes until tender but not brown. Add rice and cook for a few minutes longer, stirring constantly. Put rice and onions in a well greased 1-quart casserole. Add beef broth, mushrooms and soy sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Stir 2 to 3 times while cooking. Serves 6.

title: cinnamon butter
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep indefinitely (if kept hidden).

title: raisin sour cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 In large bowl, mix sour cream & sugar. Fold in raisins & beaten eggs.
Stir in vinegar, salt, cinnamon & cloves.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake pie for 40 minutes, or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.
Remove from oven & let cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Combine next 3 ingredients and add to butter. Cook five minutes.
Take off heat and add remaining ingredients. Stir together and spread on cookie sheet.
Let set and cut.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onions until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until a knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean (8 to 10 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes.
Top with sour cream, tomatoes and cheese, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick and easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 3-inch pan.
In mixing bowl, mix flour, 1 cup sugar, milk and baking powder.
Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Pour peaches over mixture.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup sugar over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown around the edges.
Best if served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together the sugar and flour.
Add milk and cook in double boiler until thick.
Remove from heat and add egg yolks.
Mix cocoa with enough boiling water to form paste and add to mixture. Return to heat and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked crust.
Top with 2 egg whites (beaten stiff) and brown in oven at 325°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, smoothing all lumps and place in pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: johnny cake
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, shortening and beaten egg.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in 8-inch square pan at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spinach calzones and feta cheese
directions: Oil cookie sheet or pizza pan.
With rolling pin, roll pizza dough on floured board as thick as pizza.
Spread spinach over rolled out dough.
Season with pepper flakes, raisins, Feta cheese, salt, oil and olives. Fold dough to form a pocket (log) and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 3/4 hour.

title: holiday delight cheese cake(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Mix well.
Pat into bottom of a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and flour together until light, fluffy and smooth.
Gradually add lemon juice and egg product; beat well.
Add yogurt and mix thoroughly.
Pour over prepared crust.
Loosely place foil over spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until center of cake is set. Gently run tip of knife between cake and edge of pan.
Cool to room temperature before removing from pan.
Chill.
Top with Reddi-Wip or fruit pie filling.
Has 4 grams of fat per serving.

title: irish bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Pour into greased pan (Dutch oven or 11 3/4-inch skillet).
Bake for 1 hour or until firm and brown; bake muffins at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli rice quiche
directions: Combine rice, 1 egg and 1/2 cup cheese, mixing well.
Press mixture into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Set aside.

title: party wings
directions: Fry party wings.
In saucepan, put 1/2 bottle of barbecue sauce and a whole bottle of hot sauce.
After the wings are all fried, put the wings a few at a time in the sauce.
Let set for 1 minute.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Dissolve in raisin juice the soda.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add raisins.
Add juice to which the soda has been added; add oatmeal, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: purple lady salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Chill until begins to thicken.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 9-inch square or equivalent size dish.
Top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with a few chopped nuts.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all liquids, then add rest of the ingredients.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: southwest baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse and wash beans separately.
Set aside white Northern beans only in separate bowl.
Place cleaned red and black beans in oval pan.
Cook bacon pieces until crisp; remove and drain well.
Add to beans in casserole pan.
Add all remaining ingredients except white beans and green onion tops. Gently fold all ingredients together to prevent breaking up beans. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and add white beans and green onion tops for color.
Gently fold and bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes more or until beans are bubbly.

title: saucy triple bean bake
directions: Microwave Instructions:
Place bacon in 2-quart casserole dish. Cover with paper towel.
Microwave (High) for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until crisp.
Remove bacon and set aside.
Crumble meat in drippings; add onion and green pepper.
Microwave (High), uncovered, for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until meat is no longer pink. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle onto bean mixture.
Cover casserole dish.
Microwave (High) for 10 to 11 minutes or until hot and bubbly, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Put all ingredients together.
Beat with spoon 2 minutes. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: whiskey sour punch
directions: Mix together in a large bowl and garnish with cherries, oranges or strawberries.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. In large bowl,
at
high speed, beat eggs and granulated sugar until very thick	(about	5
minutes).
At
low speed, beat in lemon juice and butter.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in milk just until mixed.
Pour
into greased 8-inch square pan.
Place pan in shallow pan
(cookie
sheet with sides) on oven rack.
Pour 1-inch hot water
into
pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until lightly
brown.
Cool
for	10 minutes and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut
into squares.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Stir in brown sugar and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° until filling is set.
Cool before serving.

title: chocolate oatmeal fudge
directions: Melt butter; add milk, cocoa and sugar.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Drop on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: dippy dip
directions: Mix cheeses, green olives, peppers, onion, mushrooms, mayonnaise and half of the black olives together.
Spread in a glass 8 x 12-inch pan.
Top with pepperoni and remaining black olives.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until melted.
Serve with taco chips.
Yields 12 servings.

title: christmas hermits
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add it.
Separate eggs and beat the yolks well.
Add to mixture. Add raisins, currants, walnuts, nutmeg, cinnamon and orange peel and mix well.
Add sifted flour and salt.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Put in can to store.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients; set aside.
In mixer bowl beat butter or margarine and shortening on medium speed, for 30 seconds.
Add brown sugar and sugar, beat until fluffy, add eggs and vanilla, mix well.
Add dry ingredients to mixture and beat until well blended.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop dough by teaspoon 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 72 cookies.

title: rice dinner special
directions: Heat oil in pan; stir in flour.
Add milk slowly, stirring until smooth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to boil.
Lower heat, cook and stir mixture longer.
Add green beans, cheese and meat.
Cook over low heat, about 20 minutes, until cheese melts, stirring to prevent sticking.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy lime pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine limeade, milk and 3/4 container of Cool Whip.
Empty into pie shell and freeze for 2 hours or until stiff.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and serve with a twist of Key lime on top.
Delicious!

title: apple cupcakes
directions: Mix ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Beat well. Fill greased muffin pan or cupcake liners 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Put powdered sugar icing on top if desired.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each. Add soda to buttermilk and spices to flour. Add flour mixture and buttermilk mixture, then mix with other mixture. Mix in raisins and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 4 well-greased cake pans. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Cool before icing.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add all liquids and mix until smooth.
Add Baker poppy seed filling and nuts.
Mix on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Turn batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 65 minutes.
Cool cake 5 to 8 minutes before removing from pan.

title: clam dip
directions: Large mushroom caps form edible containers for this meaty Italian stuffing.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate.
Mix in eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour and nuts until well blended.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, or until toothpick comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan.
Cut in squares.

title: holiday lizzies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Flour fruit and nuts with 1/2 of flour.
Add remaining flour to egg mixture, then add soda, salt, milk, whiskey and fruit; mix thoroughly. Drop from tip of spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: creamy chipped beef
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, melt margarine.
Add flour and stir until well blended.
Slowly add milk, constantly stirring.
Once this starts to thicken, reduce heat and add beef. Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper if desired. Serve over biscuits or toast.

title: jello cake
directions: Make jello with 1/2 cup less water.
Put in flat pan to gel. Boil 1 cup of pineapple juice.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and the lemon jello.
Cool in freezer.
Make Dream Whip as directed.
Add juice to Dream Whip.
Cube jello and add to Dream Whip.
Line pan with ladyfingers, then add jello and mixture.

title: chicken vegetable stir-fry
directions: Melt margarine in a large pan or wok. When hot, add onions and chicken.
Cook about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add broccoli, cauliflower, zucchini and soy sauce.
Continue cooking for 5 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Serve with rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: spicy oyster crackers
directions: Mix together Crisco oil, dressing mix and dill weed.
Pour over crackers, stirring gently.
Cover in airtight container and keep stirred for about 2 hours or overnight.
Enjoy!

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 1/2 gallon or 1 gallon plastic pitcher.
(I use a 1 gallon pitcher.)
Put in freezer and stir every 2 to 3 hours until frozen.
This recipe may be used for other flavors.

title: doralee's chicken cordon bleu
directions: Cut each breast in half.
Pound out thin.
You need two pieces of
breast
same size for one serving.
Put a piece of ham, then a
slice
of cheese on each of four slices of meat. Make
sure filling comes to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Top with remaining breast
slices,
pressing
edges
of chicken firmly together. Coat
breast
lightly with flour seasoned with salt and
pepper. Dip
in
eggs
and
milk (beaten together), then crumbs.
Repeat. Cook in hot oil.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in syrup and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover top with pecan halves.
Bake at 315° to 325° for 45 minutes.

title: apple rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
For pastry, combine flour and shortening; add enough milk to moisten flour until it will be stiff.
Chill. In a 9 x 13-inch pan add butter, 2 cups water, white sugar and vanilla.
Let this mixture get real hot and stir.
Roll pastry into a large circle.
Sprinkle with chopped apples and brown sugar. Roll this up into a roll.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch slices and put in hot mixture.
Cook slow until golden brown, about 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Heat oil
in ovenproof dish or skillet.
Saute chops quickly. Remove to a plate as they brown.
If necessary, add more oil and saute rice, onion and pepper until rice is golden brown.
Place chops on top of rice mixture.
Pour the tomatoes over everything and sprinkle with the oregano and vinegar.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Check occasionally to be sure there is plenty of liquid.
Add water, if necessary, to keep the rice from sticking.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix eggs, butter, sugar and preserves.
Add flour and mix well. Pour over fruit and nuts.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake 4 hours at 250°.
Watch cakes in about 3 hours.
Makes 2 cakes.

title: honey mustard glazed pork chops
directions: In small saucepan whisk all but pork cops until well blended. Bring to boil over low-medium heat stirring frequently. Reduce heat simmer for 2 min. Place pork chops in a 13x9-baking pan. Top chops with sauce turn to coat. Bake uncovered at 350-degrees for 25 min. or until pink is gone from meat.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Soften butter.
In mixer bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to the creamed mixture and beat until blended.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill about 1 hour.
(I do it overnight!)

title: easy crock-pot pork barbecue
directions: Put pork in crock-pot.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over shoulder and add vinegar.
Cover and simmer 12 hours.
Remove from pot and pick meat from bones.
Strain liquid and keep approximately 2 cups.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix with minced meat and return to crock-pot.
Cook on low until juice is cooked down (or cook on high setting for shorter time).
Freezes well.

title: toasted onion potatoes
directions: Rinse and brush potatoes.
Cut into large chunks.
Place soup mix and potatoes and oil in large plastic bag.
Empty potato mixture onto nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake, stirring and turning occasionally to brown completely, for 40 minutes or until brown and tender, at 450°.
Serves 8.

title: scalloped carrots with mustard-cheese sauce
directions: In a large saucepan with a steamer rack, steam the carrots for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
In a small saucepan, cook the onion in the margarine or butter for 2 to 3 minutes or until the onion is tender.
Stir in the flour, salt and dry mustard.
Stir in the milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until the sauce is thickened and bubbly, about 5 minutes.
Stir in the Cheddar cheese, dill, celery seed and pepper.
Cook and stir until the cheese is melted.
Toss the carrots with the sauce.
Or, arrange the carrots on a platter and top with the sauce.
Garnish with fresh dill, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: min's pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a small bowl, mix salt and spices until well blended.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients except pie shell until well blended.
Add spice mixture and mix thoroughly.
Place pie shell(s) on a foil-lined baking sheet.
Pour filling in shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, decrease oven temperature to 350° and bake 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: parmesan party rounds
directions: In bowl, combine mayonnaise, artichoke hearts, Parmesan cheese and red pepper.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff not dry.
Fold egg whites into cheese mixture; spoon onto bread slices.
Place on baking sheet and broil 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: tex-mex taster
directions: Mix avocados and lemon juice.
Layer avocados, sour cream, picante sauce, veggies and cheese.
Chill.

title: white chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed.
Add egg; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla. Stir in white chocolate and macadamia nuts.
Chill dough 1 hour. Drop dough by 2 tablespoons, 3 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove to wire racks to cool completely.

title: tabouli salad
directions: Soak the bulgar wheat in cold water for 30 minutes, then drain well.
Put bulgar wheat in a bowl. Add the tomatoes, mint, parsley and scallions or onions.
Pour the lemon juice, oil, salt and pepper over.
Toss lightly.
Allow to marinate before serving.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Break stems off mushrooms and chop finely.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons water.
Add 3 tablespoons liquid Butter Buds, mix chopped stems into butter-onion mixture.
Pour lemon juice over them, and stir in bread crumbs, parsley, water chestnuts.
Remove from heat source and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in egg yolk. Stuff mixture into caps.
Brush Butter Buds over each stuffed mushroom and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled beets
directions: Tie spices in cloth and boil in vinegar syrup along with beets 15 or 20 minutes to half hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple, reserving juice.
Chop apples and oranges and mix with fruit cocktail.
Mix lemon pudding with 1 cup reserved juice.
Pour over fruit and mix well. Just before serving, chop bananas and add to fruit.

title: super bowl dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Mix in cheese and chili. Stir until the cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: In 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine soup, water, rice, mushrooms and 1/2 can onions.
Arrange chicken on top.
Sprinkle with pepper and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 3 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: instant cocoa with marshmallows
directions: Mix ingredients together in large container with lid.
Use 1 tablespoon in hot milk or water.

title: hard candy lollipops
directions: You will need a candy-deep fry thermometer.
Set molds and spray with Pam on foil.
In pot, put water, syrup and sugar and stir a little.
Stir and boil.
Bring to 275° to 300°.
Quickly remove from heat and add flavoring and coloring.
Pour into molds right away.
Add seed.
Let set.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil and simmer 20 minutes; cool.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; pour in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Cook 4 cups of chicken breasts; let cool.
Pepper to taste and place in greased dish.
Mix celery soup, chicken soup, chicken broth and mixed vegetables.
Pour over chicken.
Mix self-rising flour, milk and butter.
Pour over chicken for topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: butter meltaway cookies
directions: In mixing bowl cream butter, oil and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla. Add flour, baking soda and cream of tartar. Mix well. Chill for several hours or over night.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
flatten with fork dipped in flour. Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes. Cook on wire rack.
Yield:
About 4 dozen.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: When mixture is hot, add meatballs and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello
and	chill
until it begins to thicken.
Add the other ingredients.	Mold or put in a long glass dish.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Heat buttermilk, but do not scald.
Add oil, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, dissolved in 1/4 cup warm water. Add 3 cups flour and soda; stir to make a smooth batter.
Add remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Place in a greased bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli-rice au gratin
directions: Cook broccoli florets until tender.
Cook rice until it is just done.
Melt Velveeta with milk and butter.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Combine all ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with your choice of dried onions, bread crumbs or crushed potato chips.

title: chinese crunch
directions: Slowly melt butterscotch bits.
Add noodles and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.

title: holiday beef roast
directions: Rub meat with cut cloves of garlic and dredge with flour. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place in roasting pan in which shortening has been melted.
Arrange onions and carrots around and under meat.
Place in preheated oven and roast at 325° allowing 25 to 35 minutes per pound.
(Do not turn roast with a fork.
Piercing the seared outer coat releases juices that should remain inside.
Do not baste.)
Thicken gravy after roast is done and lifted from the pan.

title: mexican salad supper
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain. Chill.

title: green eggs and ham
directions: Let each child crack an egg in the pan.
Add milk.
Add food coloring until eggs are green. Stir the whole thing together.
Add ham.
Stir and cook well.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, ground beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Serves 8.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello and
let cool.
Add undrained pineapple, other fruits, and celery.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Grease a 10 x 5-inch loaf pan and dust lightly with flour. Cream butter and gradually blend in fruit sugar; beat until light and fluffy. Then add, one at a time, three eggs; beat thoroughly after each addition. Blend or sift together flour and salt. Add gradually to the creamed mixture, blending thoroughly. Fold in halved red cherries, green cherries and grated lemon rind. Pour into prepared pan. Bake in preheated 300° oven for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: grandma's soft gingerbread
directions: Put butter and molasses over medium heat and bring to a boil. Remove and add soda; then beat well.
When cool add milk and well beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together.
Mix well. Bake in well-greased and floured pan in a 350° oven for 40 minutes. Serve warm with country butter or topped with whipped cream.
