title: santa's whiskers
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together butter or margarine and sugar. Blend in milk and vanilla or rum flavoring.
Stir in flour, chopped candied cherries and chopped pecans.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast with sugar in lukewarm water.
Add enough flour to make soft dough. Cover tightly.
Let rise until double in size. Make out in rolls and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in brine (salt and 1/2 gallon water) overnight. Drain and drop in boiling cider vinegar, 1 quart water, pickling spices and sugar.
When cucumbers turn bright green, pack in cans. Cover with hot liquid and seal.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dip meat in flour; brown in hot oil.
Add onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Combine sour cream, tomato soup, mushroom liquid and seasonings; pour over meat.
Simmer until tender, about 1 hour. Serve over hot spaghetti; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate brownie cookies
directions: First you go to the store and buy some cookies.
Then go buy some brownies.
Mix them together and there you have chocolate brownie cookies.
Yes!

title: seasoned green beans
directions: Heat beans in microwave seasoned with garlic salt.
Melt butter in small dish in microwave.
Add Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs and paprika.
Pour mixture over green beans.
Stir and serve.

title: savory meat loaf
directions: Combine chili sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, nutmeg and mustard. Heat; stir constantly.

title: creamy cheesecake
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature, mix until creamy.
Add powdered sugar/splenda and vanilla until well blended.
Whip heavy whipping cream until peaks form (fluffy).
Add to cream cheese.

title: baked ham
directions: Trim off excess fat.
Mix brown sugar and mustard. Place ham in a large baking Pan.
Spread sugar mixture over ham.
Add 1 quart of water to pan.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake 2 1/2
to 3 hours at 350 degrees or until tender.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening, eggs, sugar and carrots. Add flavoring and dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. For frosting, mix together the confectioners sugar, butter and orange juice. Spread over cooled cookies.

title: easy pizza snacks
directions: *Or whatever you prefer.

title: grammie staples mincemeat
directions: When meat has cooled. grind.
Grind apples, raisins, cranberries, and suet through the food chopper.
Mix with other ingredients, scald all together and put into jars.

title: lime jello desserts
directions: In top of double boiler add juice of pineapple, marshmallows and 1 box lime jello.
Melt and set aside to cool.
Mix with beater drained pineapple, cream cheese, mayonnaise and nuts.
When cool add marshmallow mixture.
Whip the whipping cream and add to mixture; chill.
Mix 1 box jello and 2 cups water and cool.
Pour over mixture and chill overnight.

title: orange spice cake
directions: Add this to cake, then add the raisin mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: oven beef stew(serves 8)
directions: Combine meat, vegetables, juice, tapioca, sugar and salt. Place in 11 x 7-inch pan (or larger).
Cover with foil.
Bake in 250° oven for 3 to 4 hours.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix ingredients (except flour and rhubarb), then add flour and fold in rhubarb. Add topping.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: lo-fat polynesian sandwich(heart healthy)
directions: Spread bagel or roll with butter.
Top with ham and pineapple. Broil briefly to heat.
Add cheese and broil until cheese melts. This is very popular
with teenagers! Yield: 1 serving.

title: chinese cookies
directions: Melt bits in a heavy pan over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in noodles and peanuts until well coated.
Quickly drop by teaspoon onto wax paper; put in a cool place to harden.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan; cook over low heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Add peanuts and cook until candy thermometer registers 290°.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, salt, vanilla and baking soda, mixing well.
Spread thinly onto 2 buttered cookie sheets.
Cool and break into pieces.
Yield: about 2 pounds.

title: aloo-m-kalla(golden deep-fried potatoes)
directions: Peel the whole potatoes evenly.
Arrange the potatoes in a pot.
Cover them completely with oil.
Add salt, turmeric and 1 cup of water.
Bring this to a boil over medium-to-high heat, then lower heat to low simmer.
Cover pot with lid.
Continue to simmer for 45 minutes until the potatoes have formed a golden crust.

title: lemon oat lacies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients, except powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Cover; chill 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in powdered sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until edges are light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove; cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Coat beef with flour, salt and pepper; toss with oil in 3-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
Stir once; add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix and put in pie plate or glass baking dish.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix and bake in unbaked pie shell at 325° until brown.

title: spinach milano
directions: Cook spinach, drain.
Gradually add flour to butter.
Blend well until smooth.
Add to spinach with remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Spoon into lightly greased casserole (3 quart).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or a little longer if needed.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Beat butter for 30 seconds. Add sugar. Beat until fluffy.
Add milk and vanilla. Beat well. Stir in flour, then cherries and pecans. Shape into three 7-inch long rolls.
Roll in flaked coconut to coat.
(Or, if desired, stir coconut into the dough instead of coating rolls.)
Wrap in waxed paper or clear plastic wrap. Chill thoroughly.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven about 12 minutes or until edges are golden. Remove to wire rack. Cool.
Makes about 80.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine sugar, dry milk and cocoa in a large bowl; stir well. Store in airtight container. To serve, place 1/4 cup mix in a cup. Add 1 cup boiling water and stir well.
Yields about 28 servings.

title: italian beef
directions: Combine all ingredients except meat.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over meat in a roaster.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 350° (internal meat temperature 155°).
Cool completely; save liquid.
Slice meat paper thin.
Put slices back in the juice and refrigerate overnight.
Heat and serve.
Be sure to save all the liquid and use on sandwiches.

title: chocolate turtle cheesecake
directions: In saucepan, melt caramels and milk.
Pour into crust.
With mixer, blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Slowly add and mix eggs and add chocolate morsels.
Mix well.
Pour over caramels in crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: french bake tuna
directions: Layer tomato, pepper strips, zucchini, eggplant, onion and tuna in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with parsley, lemon juice, thyme and salt and pepper, as desired.
Bake at 375° until tender.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese, then add all the rest of the ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator overnight, then shape into a ball.

title: egg bake casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in casserole dish.
Drizzle margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Insert knife as for custard.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: Brown chopped onion in pan with 1 tablespoon shortening.
Pour in pork and beans, brown sugar, catsup, water and barbecue sauce. Stir and cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes or if you prefer beans may be baked in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: brown sugar pudding
directions: Boil 3 minutes all together the brown sugar, boiling water and butter.
Mix sugar, 1 tablespoon butter, milk, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and walnuts.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot syrup.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: microwave enchilada chili bake
directions: Place beef in a 3-quart microproof casserole; break up with a spoon.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook on High 5 to 6 minutes or until beef is no longer red; drain.
Stir again to break up beef. Stir in enchilada sauce and tomato sauce.
Cook on High 3 minutes. Stir in beans, 1 cup corn chips and 3/4 cup cheese.
Cover; cook on High 6 minutes; stir.
Spread sour cream evenly over top. Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups corn chips and 1/4 cup cheese.
Cook on Medium-high for 1 to 2 minutes until sour cream is warm.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: egg casserole
directions: Layer bread on bottom (cubed) of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Layer sausage, mushrooms and cheese.
Mix eggs, mustard, salt and 2 1/2 cups milk.
Add soup to egg mixture.
Pour over bread, sausage and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut clusters
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate over hot (not boiling water.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix together well and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes about 35 clusters.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by package directions, boiling 5 minutes. (Don't overcook.)
Drain.
Mix with soup, onions, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Put into casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel potatoes and cut as desired.
Combine other ingredients in small saucepan and boil for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place potatoes in a greased baking dish and pour sauce over them and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt kelly's salad
directions: Boil and drain pasta and let cool. While cooling, combine other ingredients, reserving some Parmesan cheese. Mix with cooled pasta. Top with rest of Parmesan cheese. Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Roll the steak in flour and fry good and brown. Drain grease. Put lipton soup mix with water and pour over meat. Let simmer 45 minutes. Add potatoes, carrots, onion, bell pepper and soup. Simmer for another hour or until vegetables are done. This cooks well in a large electric skillet.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Place mixture in casserole dish.
Place sliced onions on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion, pepper, parsley and celery seed in oil.
Add garlic.
Mix remaining ingredients in separate bowl, then add to saute.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs with mixer.
Add pineapple with juice, vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Add flour and soda.
Mix by hand. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken soup with dumplings
directions: Cover several pieces of chicken with cold water.
Add 1 carrot, 1 stalk celery, 1 small onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Remove chicken and strain broth.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream the margarine and cheese together.
Add seasonings and work in flour.
Turn onto wax paper and shape into roll about 10-inches long and 1-inch in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and chill several hours.
(At this point, dough can be frozen and baked later.)

title: hamburger cheese bake casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is lightly brown and onion is tender. Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt and pepper. Remove from heat.

Meanwhile cook noodles according to directions on package; drain. Mix all the other ingredients with noodles. In a casserole dish, put a layer of noodles, then some meat sauce; repeat until all is used. Put Parmesan cheese on top. Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kristi's hamburger delight
directions: Flatten hamburger into patties.
Put cheese in the middle. Roll hamburger up and fry until about done with bell pepper. Drain grease.
Add tomato soup.
Cook on low heat until done.

title: gorp
directions: Mix in large container.
Store in airtight container.

title: cherry nuggets
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add corn syrup, egg yolks, vanilla and flour; mix well.
Chill.
Lightly beat egg whites.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip each in egg whites.
Coat with nuts. Press a cherry half, cut side down, into center of each.
Place cookies about 1 1/2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: squash or zucchini parmesan
directions: Thinly slice squash or zucchini.
Put first 6 ingredients in skillet.
Cover and cook one minute.
Uncover and cook, turning with wide spatula, about five minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Put all ingredients into stew pot and simmer for 35 minutes. Top each bowl with Parmesan cheese.

title: angel sponge pudding
directions: Cook milk, sugar and eggs in double boiler for 15 minutes. Set aside.
Dissolve gelatine in water.
Stir gelatine mixture into custard while still hot.
Cool thoroughly.
Add pineapple. Fold in whipped topping.
Crumble angel food in bottom of flat dish and pour custard mixture on top.
Chill 5 to 8 hours.

title: lobster fra diarolo
directions: Steam lobster(s) minimally and clean.
Detach claws, legs and body of lobster; add to sauce at beginning of cooking of 30 to 40 minutes.
Reserve tail and add to sauce the final 10 minutes.

title: graham nut bread
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar, baking powder, salt and nuts. Set aside. Beat eggs. Add milk, shortening and rind. Blend into crumbs mixture. Pour into a greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown. Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: lazy girl cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk and pour over melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Place fruit over this.
Then pour the juice over top.
Do not stir after you have added fruit and juices.
Bake at 375° for about 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: ranch style pea salad
directions: Toss first 4 ingredients together.
Mix sour cream, Ranch dressing and bacon bits and pour over vegetables.
Stir in cashews before serving.

title: red apples
directions: Stir all ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: low-fat raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Stir in the oats.
Combine egg whites, brown sugar, oil, milk, vanilla and raisins and add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto oiled (or Pammed) cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.
Use less flour if you prefer a thinner, flatter cookie.

title: puppy chow(people food snack)
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Pour mixture over cereal and stir.
Let cool slightly.
Put 10x sugar in bag.
Pour cereal in and shake until coated.
Excellent for kids to make!

title: raisin pudding
directions: Boil for 5 minutes the water, 2 cups white sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Cream together 1 cup sugar, margarine and eggs.
In a large bowl, combine batter and boiling mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza dessert
directions: Cut dough into small circles and lay in cookie sheet.
Press out so all cookie sheet is covered.
Bake according to directions and cool thoroughly.
Meanwhile, mix softened cream cheese, vanilla, sugar and La Creme.
Spread on cooled cookie sheet.
Lay fruit on top of all.
Cut into squares.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Combine butter flavored Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl; beat at medium speed.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough, 2 inches apart, onto baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on cooling rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: peanut butter oatmeal rounds
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop dough in rounded teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: apple danish
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in Crisco.
Beat egg yolk in measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid.
Mix well. Stir egg into flour.
Roll 1/2 of dough to fit a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cornflakes.
Add apples.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle apples.
Roll remaining dough.
Place over apples.
Seal edges.
Cut slits in top.
Brush with egg white. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well in mixer first five ingredients. Add vanilla and coconut. Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan for 50 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix frozen lemonade with Eagle Brand milk, and then add Cool Whip.
Mix	well
and
put	into
a baked and cold graham cracker crust.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: strawberry swizzle
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add cold water; chill until syrupy (about 1 hour).

title: crispy critters
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat until begins to bubble.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir.
Press into buttered pan.
Melt chips together and spread over Rice Krispie mixture.

title: potato frank bake
directions: Place hash browns in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
In a bowl, mix together soup, milk and onions.
Fold into hash browns. Spread drained green beans over the hash browns.
Put hot dogs over green beans.
Cover and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until hash browns are hot in center. Remove from heat. Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven and bake until cheese is melted.

title: brenda's any meat barbecue sauce(great for pork, beef, chicken, venison)
directions: In medium saucepan combine all ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Prebake meat for about 1/2 hour.
Pour sauce over and continue to bake until meat is tender.
Use extra sauce over rice.

title: danish toasts
directions: Peel, core and slice the apple; dip in lemon juice.
Shell and slice the hard-cooked eggs.
Lightly whip the cream and mix with mustard, mayonnaise and dill.
Remove the crusts from the slices of toast and arrange the smoked salmon slices on each piece.
Top with an apple slice and slices of hard-cooked egg.
Finally spoon on the mayonnaise mixture.

title: peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in cocoa, soda, salt and flour.
Mix well and add peanut butter chips.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Cover with tomato sauce. Bake at 350 for one hour.

title: caramel cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and butter.
Add prunes.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon. Add milk and nuts.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together eggs and oil.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon; mix together.
Add apples and nuts. (Batter will be thick.)
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Grate cheese. Defrost and drain spinach (do not cook). In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, melt butter. Beat eggs and add flour, milk, salt and baking powder. Mix well. Add cheese and well drained spinach. (Optional, 1/2 cup chopped green onions to be added with spinach.) Pour into buttered pan and bake about 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and cool until set. Cut into small squares. May be frozen. To serve, heat at 325° about 10 minutes. If cut into larger squares, this is a nice dish with ham or chicken for luncheon. It makes about 25 cocktail-size servings or 12 larger servings.

title: fruit salad(for diabetics)
directions: In saucepan, soften gelatin powder in the fruit juice.
Bring mixture to a boil to dissolve gelatin.
Remove from heat and stir in sweetener.
Fill jars, leaving 1/4-inch of space at top.
Do not process or freeze.
Add spices or coloring, if desired. Yield: 4 half-pints.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Scrub medium size whole potatoes until clean.
Boil in skins until tender.
Cut in half; arrange in baking dish, cut side down. Pour Italian salad dressing in dish, 1/8-inch deep.
Let potatoes marinate for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: greek slaw
directions: Boil water, turn heat off.
Place cabbage in water and let set for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mix in rest of vegetables and add dressing.
Serves 8.

title: sizzlin' fajitas
directions: Arrange salsa, sour cream, cilantro, olives, tomatoes, peppers and cheese in serving bowls.
Toss chicken or beef in Worcestershire sauce.
Stir-fry in hot oil.
While meat is frying, microwave tortillas, 3 to 4 at a time.
Serve in covered bowl. Remove meat from heat and serve immediately, in the pan.
While still "sizzling" scoop meat in folded warm tortillas and allow guest to layer their fajitas according to taste.
Serves 6.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Put rice in bottom of greased casserole.
Add other ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 2 1/4 hours.

title: butterhorns
directions: Add sugar and beaten eggs to yeast.
Sift flour and salt.
Mix with soft margarine or Crisco and add to first mixture.
Beat one minute.
Dough will be soft.
Place in mixing bowl and let rise in refrigerator overnight.

title: orange cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges in food grinder.
Add sugar.

title: herb mushrooms
directions: Put mushrooms in casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to casserole.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes and serve with steak or roast beef.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in oil until wilted.
In double boiler or microwave melt cream cheese and oleo.
When onions are ready, add shrimp.
Cook until pink.
To shrimp add mushrooms, seasonings and rice.
Mix well and add crab meat.
Pour cream cheese mixture into shrimp mixture.
Mix and pour into casserole dish.
Top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Melt chips, butter and milk; add nuts and vanilla. Cream together sugar, eggs, vanilla and shortening. Add sifted dry ingredients and oatmeal. Press 2/3 cookie mixture in pan (greased 10 x 16-inch). Spread on fudge mixture, then dab and spread rest of cookie mix on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Don't overbake.

title: pistachio pudding pound cake
directions: Place in deep bowl and mix at medium speed the milk, oil and water.
Add in the eggs and beat for 2 minutes or more.
Add the pudding mix and add cake mix.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 minutes.

title: flubber
directions: In large bowl, mix glue and 1 1/2 cups water by stirring slowly.
You may add food coloring here.
In a measuring cup, measure 1/3 cup water and stir in 1 teaspoon Borax.
Pour Borax solution slowly into glue mixture.
Stir slowly with spoon.
A clot will form on the spoon; keep stirring gently until clot seems to be staying same size, a minute or so.
Lift spoon.
Remove clot to a smooth surface and knead.
The more it's worked, the less watery it will become.
There should be lots of glue/water left in bowl.
Mix another dose of Borax/water; repeat procedure in same bowl.
I used 4 or 5 Borax solution applications until glue/water was used up. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Cut while still warm.

title: pudding ice cream sandwiches
directions: Mix pudding according to package.
Add whipped cream to pudding and mix.
Lay two crackers on cookie sheet close together. Layer pudding mix over the crackers.
Top with crackers and freeze until firm.
When frozen, break into sandwich. Put in container.
Serve as ice cream sandwiches.

title: maple syrup
directions: Put hot water in saucepan and boil.
Add sugar, lemon juice, butter and Mapleine; heat to boiling, stir occasionally.

title: southern peanut butter pie
directions: Combine all five ingredients.
Mix until it is all thoroughly blended.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake in 400° oven 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Chill. Top with whipped cream.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water until 1 cup of juice is left.
When juice is still warm, add the remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and bake in a flat 1/2-inch thick pan at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Spread with powdered sugar frosting and sprinkle with walnuts before cutting into squares.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount boiling salt water for 5 minutes.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in grated carrots, then add squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and butter. Spread 1/2 of mix in bottom of 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over vegetables.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated and lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: pepper swiss cheese ball(pepper compliments the nutty flavor of swiss cheese.)
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese on medium speed, scraping bowl often, until smooth (1 to 2 minutes).
Add sour cream and garlic salt; continue beating until well mixed.
By hand, stir in cheese and parsley.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Shape into flattened cheese ball or log.
Roll in pepper to coat.
Store refrigerated.

title: vegetable puff
directions: Cook frozen vegetable according to package directions (add no salt); drain thoroughly.
Place vegetable in 13 x 9 x 2- inch baking dish, spraying previously with Pam and a sprinkling of garlic.
In the meantime, combine soup and cheese; gradually add milk, mayonnaise and egg to soup mixture, stirring until well blended.
Pour over vegetable in dish.
Combine bread crumbs, butter and cheese; sprinkle over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until crumb topping is lightly browned.
Yields approximately 10 servings.

title: quick and cool summer salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and cool. Add vegetables, tuna, cheese, pickles and onion. Blend together sour cream, salad dressing, lemon juice and salt and pepper. Toss dressing with macaroni mixture. Cover and chill.

title: steamed chicken
directions: Prepare chicken for roasting.
Rub inside and outside with salt and pepper.
Rub outside with melted butter.
Place in steamer. Steam until tender.
If desired, steamed chicken may be brushed with melted butter and browned in oven.

title: swedish limpa
directions: Heat beer and honey briefly in a saucepan.
Pour into a large mixing bowl.
When lukewarm (100° to 105°) sprinkle on the yeast and let it dissolve.
Stir in salt, seeds, zest, rye flour and butter.
Beat in unbleached flour (3 to 3 1/2 cups) until you have a workable dough.
Hand knead for 10 minutes, adding flour as needed.
Place dough in a large buttered bowl to rise until doubled.
Punch the dough down and knead briefly.
Divide dough in halves and shape each half into a tight ball.
Place dough balls on a large, lightly greased, cornmeal dusted cookie sheet.
Dust the loaves with cornmeal and cover loosely with plastic.
Allow to rise again.
Test by pressing the dough with your finger, if the surface bounces back, it is not ready.
Make two 1/2 inch deep slits on the tops of the loaves with a sharp knife.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Loaves are done when they are brown and crusty and when they make a hollow sound when you tap them on the underside with your finger.
Cool on a rack.

title: ham-broccoli roll-ups
directions: Place 1 broccoli spear on 1 slice ham and roll up.
Boil rest of ham slices around broccoli spears.
Place ham roll-ups in baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over roll-ups.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes or until hot.

title: easy onion soup
directions: In covered saucepan, cook onions and garlic in butter over low heat for 20 minutes.
Add stock and wine with 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Bring to boiling.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Toast bread. Top each with sliced cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Broil for 2 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Ladle soups into 4 bowls.
Top each with a toast slice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Microwave ground beef in 2-quart casserole for 5 to 6 minutes or until brown.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cut eggplant in half.
Remove pulp and finely chop.
Add cut eggplant to meat mixture.
Cover.

title: oatmeal caramel bars
directions: Melt the caramels with the light cream in a double boiler. Combine the flour, oats, brown sugar, soda, salt and melted butter and press half of the mix in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with the chocolate chips and pecans. Pour the caramel mixture over. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until golden. Chill 1 to 2 hours before cutting.

title: mexican fried chicken
directions: Combine in paper bag the flour, chili powder and salt.
Shake chicken pieces in mix.
Fry in oil.
When brown, remove and add onion, rice, Ro-Tel tomatoes, water, chili powder and salt. Arrange chicken over rice mixture.
Cover and simmer for 35 to 40 minutes until tender and rice is done.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak the apricots in the warm water for 30 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, cream the sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in orange juice.
Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and the salt and stir into the creamed mixture just until combined.
Drain the apricots well and add with the nuts to the mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until the bread tests done.
Cool 10 minutes in the pan before removing to a wire rack.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: triple chocolate mint-cream layer cake
directions: Grease 3 (8-inch) round cake pans; line with wax paper and grease and flour wax paper. Set aside.

title: whiskey sour punch(smooth and mellow. party guests always ask for the recipe.)
directions: Four hours before serving, combine orange juice and lemonade with sugar and maraschino cherry juice.
Refrigerate.
Spear cherries and pineapple chunks on toothpicks.
Cover and chill. Thirty minutes before serving, chill punch bowl.
At serving time, combine juice mixture with whiskey and soda.
Float orange and lemon slices on top.
Place the prepared skewered cherry and pineapple garnish at the side of each serving cup.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer the following items in order: apples and orange juice.
Mix and sprinkle on top the sugar and cinnamon.
Mix, then crumble on top, the flour, sugar and margarine.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 to 55 minutes, or until done.

title: crusty baked apples(diet)
directions: Peel apples halfway down.
Put in a baking dish, pared side up.
Melt butter.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Add Sweet 'N Low (brown) and vanilla.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 425° until apples are tender.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients.
Form mixtures into large patties.
Brown in butter in a large frying pan.
Pour off grease. Pour soup and can of water over patties and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.

title: dressing
directions: Cook celery, onion and margarine over medium heat until onion is clear, not brown.
Place bread cubes in bowl.
Add the rest of ingredients and stir.
Put into a baking bowl and bake for about one hour at 350°.

title: chicken or tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.
(This is a great way to get that Thanksgiving turkey used up.)

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix cheese, milk
and lemon juice.
Add drained pineapple. Fold in Cool
Whip;
divide into 2 pie shells and chill. These pies freeze well also.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix pound cake mix, egg and spice with fork until it is all moist.
Pat in bottom of greased 8 x 11-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Add pumpkin, milk, eggs and spice until well mixed.
Pour over crust and bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add pumpkin, eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Stir together flour and next 6 ingredients.
Add to batter.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in 3-quart heavy saucepan over medium-high heat.
Bring to a full boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir well and drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Cool.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.
May be frozen.

title: punch
directions: Mix these ingredients for the base.
You may freeze the base to prepare an ice ring.
When serving, place base in punch bowl, then add ginger ale or 7-Up as desired to taste.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes until thick.
Line bottom and sides of a 3-quart bowl with vanilla wafers.
Slice 1 banana on the layer of wafers.
Next, spoon 1/3 of the pudding over the bananas.
Repeat layers and chill.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding before serving.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat margarine in a rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches in oven until melted.
Sprinkle brown sugar over margarine.
Arrange pineapple on top.
Decorate with walnut halves and cherries.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly in center, 45 to 55 minutes.
Immediately invert pan on heatproof serving plate.

title: potato salad
directions: Slip potato skins the easy way. Score raw potatoes around the center with the point of your knife.
Cook in salt and dill until done. Spear each spud with a fork and peel. Slice and then marinate them while still hot in the French dressing. Add the chopped onion and let stand until cold.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Wash broccoli and cut into bite size pieces.
Combine other ingredients in a jar, blending well.
Pour over broccoli and marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Drain well and serve chilled.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt
first
3 ingredients in microwave and stir.
Pour over Crispix
and
mix.	In
a paper bag, put 1/2 box powdered sugar. Add
candied
Crispix.
Then add other 1/2 of powdered sugar and shake.
Make sure every piece is covered well. Store in a tin. Keeps a long time.

title: chicken saltimbocca
directions: Pound chicken to 5 x 5-inch cutlets.
Place ham slice and cheese slice on each cutlet, cutting to fit.
Top with dash of sage.
Roll up, jelly roll fashion.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan and parsley.
Dip chicken in butter, then roll in crumbs.
Place in shallow baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: almond macaroons
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Roll in small pieces by hand.
Bake at 350°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, jello, oil, water, eggs and strawberries together in mixing bowl.
Pour into greased cake pan and bake at 350° until done.
Cool.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over cabbage and onion and set aside. Bring vinegar, celery seed, mustard, salt and sugar to a boil. Add oil and bring to a second boil.
Pour over cabbage and onions. Mix well and refrigerate.
This will keep two weeks.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place chicken in bottom of deep baking dish.
Spoon sour cream and soup over top of chicken.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sideline snacks
directions: Arrange fruit chunks and cheese or vegetables chunks and cheese on frilled wooden pick.
Fold salami slices in half; wrap around cheese.
Secure with filled wooden pick.

title: mexican beef-noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat in margarine.
Break up with a fork.
Add green peppers and cook 5 minutes.
Add soup, milk, most
of cheese, corn and noodles.
Put in casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Heat in oven for about 30 minutes.

title: orange pecans
directions: Boil water
and
sugar until a thin syrup forms.
Flavor with orange
rind
and vanilla.
Mix pecans into syrup and pour on greased surface.
Break into pieces while warm.

title: stuffed cornish hens
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Add remaining ingredients. Sprinkle cavity of hens with salt.
Stuff mixture into cavities. Loosely cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking 1 hour, basting occasionally with butter. Makes 6 servings.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Combine fruit and sugar and let stand 2 hours. Dissolve Jell-O| in 3 cups hot water. Cool. Combine with cranberry mixture and allow to set in 9 x 13-inch dish or other similar sized glass bowl.

title: breakfast squares
directions: Fry sausage and bacon.
Drain and crumble.
Butter 11 x 14-inch dish.
Spread half the cubed bread and 1 cup cheese in bottom.
Add sausage and bacon and rest of bread and cheese.
Beat eggs; mix rest of ingredients and pour over casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes, uncovered, until no moisture is left.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Add boiling water to syrup to make 1 1/4 cups. Dissolve jello in the hot liquid. Chill until partially set. Fold in cranberry sauce, orange zest, orange sections and pineapple. Whip heavy cream and fold in. Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold or bowl. Chill until set.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: On lightly floured surface, roll out pastry to a 12-inch circle.
Line a 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish with the pastry. Trim to 1/2-inch beyond edge.
Flute edges, line shell and fill with dry beans.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven. Remove foil and beans.
Reduce oven to 325°.

title: butterfly bits
directions: Spread cream cheese in middle of celery. Use 2 pretzels for wings and 2 pieces of pretzel for antennas.

title: honey-citrus cooler
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags.
Steep for 5 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Stir in honey.
Add cold water and fruit juices. Chill for 1 hour.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown meat, onions and celery.
Drain.
Add other ingredients. Place in oven and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cover last half hour.

title: mona's chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
In saucepan, cook carrots, tomatoes, onion and chicken.
Make spaghetti. Drain vegies from broth. Save broth.
Add mixture to spaghetti. Add a small bit of broth. Add Velveeta cheese. Stir well and serve.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and add to it the brown sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Beat until fluffy.
Add the flour and blend together.
Mixture will be quite thick.
Spread into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with the chocolate chips and put back in oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with nutmeats.
Cut while warm.
Makes about 2 dozen bars.

title: party quiche squares
directions: Prepare pie crust according to directions.
Roll out on floured surface to 16 x 11-inch rectangle.
Arrange on bottom of ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.

title: kung pao chicken
directions: In a small glass or stainless steel mixing bowl, combine soy sauce, sherry, garlic and ginger root.
Add chicken and turn to coat. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.

title: aunt eva's cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add margarine, eggs and vanilla to dry ingredients mixture, one ingredient at a time.
Mix in lightly (optional) raisins and coconut.
Use about one heaping tablespoonful for each cookie.
Press flat before baking.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.
Makes about 3 dozen large cookies.

title: chili dip
directions: Layer all ingredients in ungreased glass pie pan.
Heat in microwave for 4 minutes. Serve with Tostitos or corn chips.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix and drizzle over the salad.

title: macaroni and cheese goulash
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions.
Drain excess liquid from tomatoes, but do not squeeze dry; cut into small pieces.
Drain vegetables.
Mix all ingredients well; place into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese or bread crumbs.

title: grace's mom's chocolate crackles
directions: Melt chocolate.
Blend in oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix.
Add nuts.
Mix.
Chill dough overnight. Shape into balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Peel and layer potatoes with thin strips of bell pepper and pimento.
Make sauce of milk, cheese, flour and margarine.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake about 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: party dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Let sit about 1 hour before serving.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together in gallon container and finish filling with water if it lacks any being full.
Chill before serving.

title: no crust cheesy salmon pie
directions: Beat together eggs, Bisquick and milk.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in quiche dish or 8 x 12-inch glass pan at 400° for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings; low-fat.

title: christmas holly cookies(a no bake favorite)
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Add vanilla and green food coloring.
Stir and add corn flakes.
Continue stirring until corn flakes are well coated.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Put on three red hots (cinnamon candies) to resemble sprig of holly.
Let dry a couple of days.
Makes about 25.

title: apple cake with chocolate chips
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil until smooth, then take all other ingredients with the exception of the chips, nuts and apples. Once eggs, sugar and oil are smooth, mix by hand the apples, nuts and chips.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy dessert
directions: Mix margarine, nuts and flour and press into oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients one at a time.
Make 3 or 4 layer cake. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 350° about 50 minutes in greased loaf pans, sprinkled with flour.
Makes 2 loaves (8 x 4 x 3-inches pan size).

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt paraffin and chocolate chips together in medium bowl in microwave. Set aside, but keep warm. Mix until smooth the sugar, margarine and peanut butter. Roll into balls about marble size. Dip into hot chocolate and place on wax paper to dry.

title: mozzarella meat pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender. Add tomato paste, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings; mix well.
Place in 9-inch pie plate; press against edge.
Flute edge.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: helen grice's buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: collards
directions: Put water, salt and salt pork in a large cooking pot (10 to 12-quart size).
Boil for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Fry out fatback and add to pot, reserving cracklings.
Prepare collards by stripping large leaves from stalk.
Wash leaves thoroughly and add to pot of prepared boiling water. Turn heat down to medium and cook until collards are tender.
Cooking time may vary for summer collards (3 hours) to winter collards (2 hours).

title: incredible edibles
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and pat into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt semi-chocolate bits and spread over mixture.
Chill until firm enough to cut.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix and put into a graham cracker crust; chill and serve.

title: microwave green beans
directions: Microwave frozen green beans and water in a 2-quart casserole dish, 15 minutes, or until tender.
Stir once during cooking. Drain.

Place cream cheese, salt and garlic salt in a bowl and microwave approximately 1 minute or until cheese is very soft. Gradually add the milk to the cream cheese and stir until smooth. Microwave another 1 to 2 minutes, stirring once while cooking. Blend sauce until thoroughly mixed and pour over green beans. Stir lightly and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, mix well.
Fold in raisins, walnuts and apples.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic and red pepper.
Spread evenly in a 9 or 10-inch quiche dish or pie pan.
Spread pizza sauce over the top.
Sprinkle with pepperoni green onions and green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes to melt cheese and heat thoroughly.

title: chicken and equsi (african)
directions: Brown chicken on all sides in oil in skillet.
Drain off oil after cooking chicken.
In the same skillet, add onions, pepper, water, tomato sauce, Tabasco sauce and salt.
Cover.
Simmer for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Add additional water if necessary.
Serve with hot cooked rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: magic bars
directions: Mix margarine and crumbs.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour milk over crumbs.
Sprinkle chips, coconut and nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tortilla black bean casserole
directions: Combine onion, green pepper, tomato, picante, garlic and cumin.
Bring to a boil and heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in beans. In a casserole dish, spread 1/3 bean mixture, 1/2 tortillas, 1/2 cheese and repeat.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, green onions and sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit and cottage cheese salad
directions: Fold together all ingredients.
Do not add water to gelatin! Chill in the refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Change flavors by using another flavor of gelatin.
Omit mandarin orange slices.
You may fold in some of the fruit to match the jello flavor.
Easy, fast and nourishing.

title: mother's tomato soup
directions: Sieve tomatoes; add cloves, onion, salt and sugar.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove onion and cloves. Cream margarine and flour and mix a little of the tomato mixture into it.
Then blend into larger tomato mixture.
Bring to a boil again and add soda.
Add tomato mixture to warm milk and reheat.

title: jalapeno-green chili sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bring to a boil and cook for at least 1 hour.
Pour into jars and seal. If you want to pressure this sauce, get it to boiling and cook for a few minutes.
Pour into jars and pressure for 10 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.

title: after school pick-me-ups
directions: On a plate, arrange 4 to 5 vanilla wafers, flat side up.
With a spoon, spread peanut butter on each wafer thick enough to hold raisins pressed in.
Have fun pressing raisins, chips or nuts into the peanut butter in any design wanted. Serve with milk and lots of napkins!

title: filled cookies
directions: Cream shortening, lard and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, dry ingredients and sour cream.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut cookies.
Put filling on one cookie; cover with another.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Filling can be jam or any filling you desire.

title: cream cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Crush herbs small.
Mix with other ingredients.
Spread on crackers of you choice.
Sprinkle with paprika for color.
Takes 5 minutes or less to make.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Mix ingredients into dough you can handle.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut out with cookie cutters.
Cook about 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: broccoli-peanut salad
directions: Place broccoli flowerets in a bowl and add onions, pimientos, peanuts and raisins.
Mix honey and mayonnaise, then add to broccoli mixture and toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill 2 hours. This is one of my favorite salads.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add color and vanilla.
Mix milk, vinegar and soda.
Add dry ingredients; mix at low speed.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, depending on size of cake pan.

title: hot fruit
directions: Drain fruit well. Mix in baking dish. Melt sugar, butter and cinnamon together. Pour over fruit. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch size. Cook in skillet the beef and onion. Stir until brown. Drain. Stir in the seasoning mix. Spread meat mixture in pie plate. Top with chilies. Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth. Pour into plate. Bake 25 minutes. Top with tomatoes and cheese. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer, if needed. Cool 5 minutes. Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes, shredded lettuce and shredded cheese, if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus.
Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Beat eggs; add to milk.
Pour over asparagus.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or microwave 9 to 10 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Warm
milk
and
marshmallows
on low heat together and pour over other ingredients.
Pour into greased Pyrex dish and cool in refrigerator.
Serve cold or at room temperature.

title: pasticcio lasagnette(messy lasagna)
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Wash the mushrooms well under lukewarm water, then soak them in beef broth until ready to use. Puree the onion, carrot and celery together in a food processor or blender.
Bring the water and 2 tablespoons of the salt to a boil in a stockpot or kettle over medium heat for the pasta.
Heat 1/4 cup of the olive oil in a saucepan and melt 1 tablespoon of the butter in it.

Add the veggie mixture, parsley and basil. Cook 5 to 6 minutes, stirring or until veggies are softened. Add the red wine and cook until it evaporates, about 2 minutes. Add the beef and mix well with all the other ingredients. Cook over a low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: amish cake
directions: Mix together by hand and pour into a greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: orange french toast
directions: Spray casserole dish with butter spray. Arrange bread in dish. Crowd pieces, if needed. Mix first 7 ingredients together well and pour over bread. Let this soak awhile and then turn bread pieces over. Sprinkle with nuts. Cover and put in refrigerator overnight. Brush with melted butter. Bake at 350° until puffed and slightly browned on top. Dust with confectioners sugar and serve with syrup, jelly, etc. Good with sausage or bacon or other breakfast things.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix sugar, Miracle Whip and vinegar well. Add broccoli and cauliflower. Mix and refrigerate. Add bacon and sunflower seeds immediately before serving.

title: cheddar-beer spread
directions: Mix until smooth 'n serve on crackers.

title: chocolate pecan caramels
directions: Line a 13 X 9 X 2 inch pan with foil; butter the foil with 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips.
Set aside.
In a heavy saucepan over medium heat, melt remaining butter.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in milk.
Cook, constantly stirring until candy thermometer reads 248° (firm ball stage) remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan (do not scrape saucepan).
Cool completely before cutting.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, peanut butter, pecans and vanilla; mix well.
Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour. Shape heaping teaspoon of mixture into 1-inch long eggs. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips with paraffin wax in top of a double boiler over medium low heat.
Use toothpicks to dip eggs in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper lined baking sheets to harden.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 6 dozen eggs.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Chop onion and brown with ground beef and drain fat.
Add soup, ketchup, Worcestershire, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in grated cheese and macaroni.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Cut cabbage finely.
Add salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Then squeeze out.
Add carrots and green pepper.

title: belgian waffles
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm milk.
Stir to dissolve.
Beat egg yolks and add to yeast mixture with vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Add to liquid ingredients.
Stir in melted butter and combine thoroughly.
Beat the egg whites until stiff. Carefully fold into batter and let mixture stand in a warm place until it doubles in bulk.
Use 1/2 cup mix per waffle.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add margarine and syrup.
Stir.
Add pecans and pour into pie crust. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: gazpacho
directions: Core and seed the tomatoes.
Peel and seed the cucumber.
Stem and seed the peppers.
Dice enough of the tomatoes, cucumber and peppers to make 6 tablespoons of each for garnish.
Cut the remainder, along with the onion, into chunks.
Tear bread into pieces.
Combine batches of the vegetable chunks, bread and the remaining 6 ingredients in a blender or food processor; process until almost smooth.
Pour into a bowl.
Cover; refrigerate about 1 hour.
Garnish each bowl with diced tomato, cucumber and green pepper.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus; mix juice with soup. Layer crackers, asparagus and cheese. Pour soup mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat egg and add milk, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour and add soda, salt and baking powder.
Then add a heaping cupful of lard; knead well.
Roll thin and cut.
Bake in a hot oven until brown.

title: blueberry or cherry torte
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating whites until stiff peaks form.
Combine nuts, crackers, baking powder and salt. Add dry ingredients to egg
white mixture. Add vanilla.
Pour into greased pie plate. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes or until crust is very dry.
Cool and add pie filling. Top with Cool Whip.

title: freezer tomato sauce
directions: Place tomatoes in a 12-quart pan.
Add onions, shredded carrots, parsley, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring slowly to a boil, stirring often.
Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Cool slightly. Measure 3 cups at a time into blender.
Cover blender and blend at low speed for 1 minute.
Sauce may be thawed and used over pasta, meat or in any dish requiring tomato sauce.
Keeps 1 year in freezer.

title: aunt hap's dressing
directions: Blend well. Store in refrigerator. Excellent on fresh greens.

title: cabbage stir fry
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet or wok at high heat 3-4 minutes. Add cabbage, bell pepper, and onions. Stir fry 7-10 minutes or until crisp tender or to desired degree of doneness. Add lime juice, salt and pepper.

title: peppermint dessert
directions: Line pan with 1/2 crushed wafers. Mix first 4 ingredients together and pour over wafers.
Top with remaining wafers. Refrigerate at least overnight.
Freezes well.

title: tapenade dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil in food processor until smooth. With motor running, dribble oil in to make a thick spread. Put in bowl and cover.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Will keep 1 week.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Allow pie shells to thaw approximately 20 minutes.
Prick the bottom crust with a fork.
Pick off chicken in small pieces and place into bottom crust.
Add the soup and mixed vegetables.
Make slits in top crust and then place onto the pie, molding edges of top and bottom crusts together.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: cheese and vegetable omelet
directions: Cut pepper into 1/4-inch thick rings.
Thinly slice onions; dice zucchini.
Cut Swiss cheese and Mozzarella cheese into 1-inch chunks.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 10-inch round baking dish. In skillet over medium heat, in hot butter, cook pepper, onion and zucchini until tender.
Remove vegetable mixture to a baking dish and top with cheese.
In a bowl beat eggs and pepper until blended.
Pour egg mixture over ingredients in a baking dish. Bake 30 minutes or until eggs are set and top is browned.
Makes 8 main dish servings.

title: spiced cranberry sauce
directions: Wash cranberries and let drain, then dissolve sugar and water in saucepan.
Add cranberries, cinnamon, cloves and lemon juice. Cook well over medium heat.
If berries pop too much, lower heat and cook until all berries are mashed.
Remove from heat. Dissolve 1 envelope of plain gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add to sauce and mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
May be stored in small containers and freeze for use in the spring.
Makes nice Christmas remembrances.

title: orange refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening and add sugars gradually, beating constantly. Add egg and beat well.
Stir in orange juice and rind.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Form into four rolls, wrap in waxed paper or plastic wrap and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
If carefully wrapped, rolls will keep for 3 to 4 weeks.
Cut in 1/8-inch slices and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Heat soup to boiling.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir until jello dissolves.
Add cream cheese.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: aunt mary's chili sauce
directions: Peel and quarter tomatoes.
Let stand at least 2 hours to drain off juice so it won't take so long to cook down.
Four times this recipe will net about 7 to 8 pints.
Mix all ingredients and cook until thick as desired (6+ hours).
Cook slowly to prevent scorching.
Keep stirring regularly throughout cooking.
Place in clean, hot jars.
Seal and water bath for 15 to 20 minutes.
Very good served with roast beef or pork.

title: cherry pie filling salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in pie filling.
Pour into pie filling.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.
Melt cream cheese and marshmallows together.
Cool completely.
Add Dream Whip (or Cool Whip).
Spread over jello and sprinkle with nuts.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put oleo, brown sugar and Karo syrup in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Take out and pour over popped popcorn in a large sack. (It helps to spray sack with Pam.)
Shake up and put in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Shake again and put on High for 1 minute. Shake again and put on High for 30 seconds.

title: low-fat cheese and crab quiche
directions: Arrange cheese evenly in pastry shell.
Top with crab flakes and green onions.
Combine egg substitute, evaporated skim milk and spices.
Pour evenly over crab flakes.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until set.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, potatoes, sugar, yeast and salt in large bowl.
Heat water and butter until very warm (125° to 130°); stir into yeast mixture.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough; knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Divide dough into 16 equal pieces; form into balls.
Place in 2 greased 8 or 9-inch round cake pans (or can be placed in one 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan).
Cover; let rise in warm, draft-free place until doubled in size, about 20 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour on rolls, if desired.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove from pans; cool on wire racks. Yields 16 rolls.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, fruit cocktail, soda and salt together. Beat 2 minutes.
Pour in greased 14 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
On top of raw batter, sprinkle brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done (approximately 30 minutes).

title: no-bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugars; bring to boil.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and Special K.
Mix well and drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: pretzel salad
directions: In a large pan put pretzels, sugar and oleo.
Press down all over evenly.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix and beat cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel layer and refrigerate.
Mix strawberries and add Jell-O.
Cool until almost jelly texture and pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate until set.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Stir 1 tablespoon milk into cream cheese; set aside.
Prepare pudding with 2 cups milk.
Whip cream cheese mixture.
Add grated lemon peel and lemon juice; whip into pudding mix.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip.
Reserve a few strawberries for garnish; stir the rest into mixture.
Pour into graham crust; decorate with reserved strawberries.
Chill for several hours.

title: butterflied garlic shrimp
directions: Heat butter in large frying pan.
Add shrimp and cook 2 minutes on each side over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and season well; continue cooking 1 minute.
Stir in green pepper and diced lemon; cook 1 more minute.
Correct seasoning, add parsley and paprika.
Mix and serve.
Serves 4.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and congeal.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into 1 inch balls.
Place on greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in single layer in a baking dish.
Combine oil, lemon juice, oregano or tarragon and garlic powder; brush on chicken.
Cover and bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove cover and brush with lemon-oil mixture.
Bake another 20 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Serve.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Heat the pineapple and cherry juices and dissolve jello in it. Add Coca-Colas.
Put jello in refrigerator and let it begin to thicken.
Add rest of ingredients and let this thicken before serving.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Sift together first six ingredients.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients and butter. Mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts.

title: to yeshua's surprise
directions: Cut Worthington vegetarian hot dogs and cheese into thirds. Wrap cheese around hot dogs.
Separate biscuits and wrap individual biscuits around hot dogs and cheese.
Place in baking pan.
Put into preheated oven at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Cook pie shells and let cool.
Melt butter and brown coconut and pecans.
Then mix next 3 ingredients and pour 1/4 of white mixture in each shell.
Then
pour caramel and then pecans and then repeat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine flour and coffee granules in a large bowl. Add brown sugar, cinnamon and salt; stir well. Cut in butter with a pastry blender until crumbly. Press half of crumb mixture into 9-inch square pan; set aside. Combine sour cream and baking soda, stirring well. Add to remaining crumb mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moist. Add egg, stirring gently to combine. Pour sour cream mixture over crumb crust in pan; sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook cabbage 15 minutes.
Roll up mixture in the leaves.
Pour 2 cans tomato sauce and a little water to cover rolls.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sugar-free spicy tea mix
directions: Put all ingredients into a 1-quart jar and shake thoroughly.

title: perfect dinner rolls
directions: Add yeast in big bowl; add water.
Let set 10 minutes.
Add warm milk, sugar and salt; stir until sugar and salt are dissolved.
Add oil, then add flour and mix until flour is taken up.
Put on well floured board and sprinkle top with flour and let it set for 10 minutes.
Knead until springy.
Put in oiled bowl; oil top of dough.
Cover and rise for 1 hour.
Punch down dough on floured board.
Pull off roll size bits of dough.
Shape into rolls and put on cooking sheet.
Oil tops of rolls and let rise 45 minutes.
Cook in 425° oven about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 35 rolls.
You can half this recipe by using 2 packages of yeast and 1/3 cup water, then half everything remaining.

title: trifle
directions: Drain off all juices.
Cut up fruit into chunks.
Mix all fruit together.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Slice cake about 1/2 inch thick.
Cover bottom of deep bowl with cake. Sprinkle with 1 to 2 tablespoons of cream sherry.
Cover cake with layer of fruit.
Cover fruit with layer of pudding.
Top with another layer of cake, sherry, fruit, pudding, etc.
Refrigerate. Just before serving, top with 1 large container of Cool Whip.

title: coffee cake
directions: Layer bread balls in a sprayed Bundt pan.
Pour melted margarine over dough balls.
Pour pudding mix over dough balls. Combine the brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle over pudding mix. Cover with wax paper or Saran Wrap lightly.
Let rise on the counter overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes, then turn onto a cookie sheet to cool.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in dish.
Mix sugar and flour; sprinkle over pineapple.
Pour 1/3 cup pineapple juice over this mixture.
Put grated cheese on top of this.
Make topping of crackers and oleo. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: sauteed scallops
directions: In a large skillet or wok heat the olive oil.
Quickly saute the scallops.
Add garlic, salt and pepper and breadcrumbs.
Toss lightly and serve immediately.
Decorate with chopped parsley.

title: orange sherbet dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add orange sherbet and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Add other ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12.

title: knoephlis (german noodles)
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour and salt. Beat eggs in separate bowl with fork; beat in flour mixture with wooden spoon. Add water to make soft dough (barely runs off edge of bowl). Add remaining salt to boiling water; bring to rolling boil. Tilt bowl until dough reaches edge. As it starts to run off, take a silver knife and slice along edge of bowl, allowing dough to drop into boiling water. Cook about 5 minutes; drain. Pour melted butter over cooked noodles. Add bread crumbs.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients into large bowl: peaches, sugar, tapioca, lemon juice and butter.
Let stand while making pastry. Pour in fruit mixture.
Bake on lower rack at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dirt n' rocks
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package.
Add Cool Whip and mix together.
Crush cookies coarsely and add to mixture.
Fold cookies and chill.

title: sweet vinegar dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve over any salad.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla into saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full rolling boil. Boil briskly for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Serve hot over cake or ice cream. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: fried fruit balls
directions: Set electric frypan to 220° or use medium heat on stove.
Melt butter and add dates, stirring constantly until thick, shiny and clear.
Cream eggs and sugar; add to date mixture and cook.
Cool; then add remaining ingredients except coconut.
Form into small balls (golf ball size) and roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: tuna dill spread
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Use as sandwich filling or spread on crackers.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: four bean salad
directions: Simmer wax beans, green beans and carrots (put carrots on bottom of saucepan) in water or liquid from beans (just enough to cover) for 15 minutes. Drain and cool.
Add kidney beans and black-eyed peas.
Combine the remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour the oil mixture over the beans.
Cover and chill before serving.
Serves 12 to 15.
For smaller servings, recipe can be cut in half for smaller amount.

title: cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch (or flour) and salt in top of double boiler.
Stir in cold milk.
Cook over boiling water until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir a little of the hot mixture into slightly beaten egg yolks; add to remaining mixture in double boiler.
Cook for 2 minutes more, stirring constantly.
Cool and stir in vanilla for cream pie.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: chicken milk gravy
directions: In a large skillet, mix chicken drippings (fat) with flour. Let cook until it bubbles.
Add milk, stirring while you add it so it will not lump.
Stir well to blend.
Add salt and sprinkle with pepper.
Cook and stir until mixture is smooth and thick.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients well and shape into meatballs.
Brown them and then add:

title: peach dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread cake mix on top of filling.
Pour margarine on top of cake mix.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour.

title: tropical fruit freeze drink
directions: Blend all in blender.
Add crushed ice until you reach the consistency you want.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry sausage, onions and peppers; leave in oil.
Add 2 more tablespoons oil.
Add tomato sauce, crushed tomatoes, garlic, parsley, oregano, basil and sugar to taste.
Simmer several hours to thicken (do not drain oil).
Freezes well.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an oblong 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and shortening in microwave for 2 minutes; set aside. Beat sugar and eggs in large bowl.
Add chocolate mixture and mix in.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; stir in.
Mixture will be thick.
Mix in nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 30 minutes, until top has a dull crust.
A slight imprint will be left when top is touched lightly with finger.
Cool before cutting.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Bring oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper to a boil and pour over the first 7 ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight or the day before you plan to use it.

title: best ever carrot cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix all the ingredients in order given. Blend thoroughly. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch well-greased and floured baking pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 minutes. When cooled, spread with cream cheese frosting.

title: fran's pot roast
directions: Peel potatoes; cut in 4 equal parts.
Cut/chop carrots into little larger than bite size.
Chop onions in small pieces.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes.
Remove from oven. Reduce heat to 325°.

title: russian tea
directions: Put tea in spice container or cloth bag.
Place in boiling water and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove bag.
Heat fruit juices; add sugar.
Add to tea.
This serves about 20 people.

title: goo goo cake
directions: Mix and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips with flour; stir into batter.
Cook in large sheet cake pan 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except crackers) in casserole dish.
Break crackers in small squares and place on top of mixture; dot each piece of cracker with butter.
Bake in oven until crackers are brown and mixture is firm at 350°.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cream together margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in oats, rice, cereal and coconut.
Roll into balls and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Place	frozen	(or
unfrozen)	hamburger
in
nonstick skillet sprayed with Pam.
Cover and place over very low heat. In about
ten	minutes,
turn the meat over and sprinkle both sides liberally
with
Mrs.
Dash.
Cooking
time
depends on whether it was frozen or not.
When frozen meat thaws, cut it (with
a spatula) into 4 pieces to hasten cooking.
When it is done,
drain thoroughly
and
add the tomato sauce and water. You may also add more Mrs.
Dash at this time.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat
and
drain	off
fat.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, onions, carrots, celery, barley, beef granules, salt and pepper.
Bring
to	a boil and simmer, covered, for 1 hour or when vegetables
are tender.
(Cabbage and/or kidney beans may also be added.)

title: microwave broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Top with cheese and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Add crumbs.
Microwave on High 1 minute.

title: cranberry plus relish
directions: Chop cranberries in a food processor, then add oranges and chop.
Add remaining ingredients; pulse for several seconds to blend.
Chill several hours before serving.
Yield:
7 1/2 cups.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add juice from orange and pineapple with enough water to make one cup.
Add thawed orange juice and fruit.
Chill until set.

title: cool pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles.
Add all ingredients in large bowl.
Stir.
Add bottle of Italian dressing.
Ranch Italian tastes very good in this recipe.
Before serving add Parmesan cheese.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all together and store in container.
Use about 2 teaspoons mix to each cup hot water.
Makes 1 quart of mix.

title: fried lumpia
directions: Saute ground pork for 5 minutes, constantly stirring.
Put pork in bowl and mix in all vegetables, onion, salt and pepper. Wrap mix in lumpia wrapper to desired size.
Deep fry.
Makes 15 to 20 pieces.

title: warm cheese dip
directions: Spread these ingredients in layers on a large platter:

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, honey and cinnamon and sweet potatoes.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popcorn in brown bag.
Put all ingredients except baking soda in bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 or 4 minutes stirring each minute until it comes to a boil.
Stir well, put in microwave for 2 more minutes.
Take out and add baking soda and stir well.
Pour over popcorn in bag and shake as you pour.
Put bag in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake well and microwave for 45 seconds.
Pour on cookie sheet.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Combine soup and cream.
Stir in carrots and squash mixture. Combine stuffing with butter.
Spread half of the dressing in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Place graham crackers over foil on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle pecans on top of crackers.
Cook remaining ingredients rapidly for 2 minutes.
Spoon on top of graham crackers.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet onion casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Place alternate layers of sliced onions, potato chips and cheese.
Mix soup and milk; pour over top. Sprinkle top with cayenne pepper and bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 8.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Cut chicken in small strips or bite size pieces.
Place in dish; sprinkle with ginger.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Add seasoned salt, brown sugar and pepper; mix well.
Heat oil in wok or nonstick skillet.
Add chicken mixture.
Stir-fry until almost done.
Add onion, bell pepper and soy sauce.
Stir-fry until chicken is tender.
Sprinkle lemon juice over mixture.
Remove from heat.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sloppy joes barbecue
directions: Combine and cook 1/2 hour.
Serves about 10 on buns.

title: old style buttermilk biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse cornmeal.
Stir in
buttermilk with a fork until soft dough is formed.

title: sour cream squash with two cheeses
directions: Cut squash into 1/4-inch slices.
Bring 2 cups water to a boil.
Add squash, salt and sugar; cover saucepan and cook over moderate heat for 20 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: crab imperial
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heat butter in pan and saute pepper until wilted.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add crab meat; mix gently. Place in ramekins or pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until bubbling.

title: fullabull's toasted pecans
directions: Place pecans in shallow pan in 200° oven.
When pecans take on a shiny appearance, add melted oleo.
Stir to coat nuts, salt to taste while stirring.
Put pecans back in oven for at least 2 hours.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Add rest of ingredients.
Toss, cover and refrigerate for minimum of 3 to 4 hours.
Makes enough to serve 8 to 10 people.

title: grapefruit and port wine jelly
directions: In a large heavy pan, mix wine and sugar.
Bring to a full boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add Certo and grapefruit juice.
Fill jars and seal.
Makes 9 half pints.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add some of the juice if necessary. Serve with crackers.

title: fiesta burritos
directions: Combine taco mix, tomato juice and oil.
Mix well and set aside.
Cook beef until brown; drain.
Stir in beans and 1/2 cup tomato juice mix.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Place 1/4 cup beef mixture and 2 1/2 tablespoons cheese on center of each tortilla. Roll up and place seam side down in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour extra juice over tortillas.
Cover (with foil) and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle with lettuce, if desired.
We serve with sour cream.

title: barbecue tuna
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook on top of stove on medium heat until desired thickness.
Serves 4.

title: wine marinated venison steaks
directions: Put the brown sugar between the steaks in a crock.
Add wine to cover the steaks and allow to stand for 24 hours.
The meat may now be cooked in any manner, i.e. broiled, etc.

title: greek ground beef with rice
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
When some grease accumulates, add onion and cook until soft.
Drain off grease.
Add rest of ingredients (except rice) and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie(simple to make, rich and delicious.)
directions: Mix ice cream and peanut butter until completely blended.
Add sherry and blend completely.
