Pour into pie crust and top with chopped nuts. Freeze 4 to 6 hours. Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: french bread with clam dip
directions: Cut off top of round loaf and scoop out bread in bite size chunks, leaving a little bread around the crust.
Place in a Baggie and seal.
Mix all the ingredients and place in the scooped out loaf.
Place top on bread and wrap tightly in aluminum foil.
Bake at 225° for 3 hours.
Serve on a tray with reserved bread chunks for dipping.
When most of the dip is gone, pull bread apart and eat crust.
This is delicious with crab also!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed.
Gradually add whipped topping and powdered sugar; beat until smooth.
Freeze at least 8 hours or let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: chocolate chip cookies(original nestle toll house)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto cookie sheet initially lightly sprayed with Pam. Bake 8-10 minutes.	Makes about 5 dozen.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly and pour into buttered dish.

title: cayenne cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients. Shape into large roll or divide and make 2 rolls. Roll cheese roll in chili powder until coated well. Serve as spread on cracker of choice.
Particularly good with Ritz or Town House crackers.

title: onion pretzels
directions: Melt margarine and add soup mix.
On a cookie sheet, break the pretzels into pieces.
With a tablespoon, drizzle the onion soup mixture over the pretzels.
Bake at 275° for 10 to 15 minutes. Store in a container lined with paper towels.

title: magic chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in milk over low heat.
When dissolved, remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Pour into a buttered dish.
Cut into squares.

title: honey peanut apple dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Beat in the peanuts, honey and vanilla until combined.
Serve with apples.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: braum's sherbet punch
directions: Directions would be the same as for Orange Punch. Don't know how many this would serve.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix pineapple and cheese in bowl.
Mix flour and sugar. Combine two mixtures and place in casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs and pour melted margarine or butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (uncovered).
Can be frozen.
Serve hot or cold.

title: fruit sauce
directions: Drain pineapple; add enough water to make 3 cups.
Mix with pudding.
Cook and stir until it comes to a boil.
Add to pineapple or any other fruit you like.
Keeps bananas from turning brown for a few days.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: old fashioned stewed sugar(pull candy)
directions: Mix ingredients and stir over high heat until it reaches boiling point.
Reduce heat to medium-high when boiling good. Cook to hard-ball stage.
Grease platter and pour out to cool. When cool enough to handle, grease hands and pull.
Continue until white and hard.
Twist out to desired size on table and cut or break into desired lengths.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Cut stems and tips off artichokes and remove all small leaves around the stem at the bottom.
Mix in a bowl the ham, salt, pepper, oil, water, egg, parsley, cheese and bread crumbs together until moist.
Press artichokes on a hard surface so the leaves spread open a little. Fill the center of the artichokes and in each leaf.
Place in a saucepan with enough water to cover artichokes halfway.
Cook slowly for about 40 minutes until tender.
May be eaten hot or cold.

title: angel food cake with strawberry sauce
directions: Cut 8 strawberries in fans for garnish, slice remaining. Combine preserves, orange peel and juice.
Heat until preserves melt.
Decorate cake with berry fans and mint leaves.
Serve with strawberry sauce.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Put pecans in 1 1/2-quart microwave dish.
Put little chunks of margarine on top of pecans.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: quick and easy muffins
directions: Mix together all ingredients; stir by hand until moistened. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with wax paper.
Mix pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour in pan.
Add dry ingredients. Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole with ham
directions: Blend butter and flour in saucepan. Add mushroom soup and cook until thick. Stir in mustard. Combine asparagus, peas, eggs and ham in 2-quart greased casserole dish. Pour mushroom sauce over all. Mix bread crumbs with cheese. Spread over top of casserole. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until casserole is brown and bubbly. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Have sausage at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients and form balls.
Bake at 375° until browned, turning during baking time.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients into a firm ball.
Chill.
Roll on floured board until 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with plain or fancy cutter.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: tangy beef-vegetable stew
directions: Place potatoes, carrots and onions in a large slow cooker. In a large skillet brown beef in oil.
Place over vegetables. Sprinkle with flour.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water. Stir in vinegar, ketchup, horseradish, mustard and sugar; pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover and cook on high for 5 hours. Add peas, corn and mushrooms.
Cover and cook on high for 45 minutes.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: thimble cookies
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Thoroughly beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
With wooden spoon gradually work in flour until blended.
Chill if necessary before shaping.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place balls about 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Using a lightly floured thimble, press a small hole about 1/4-inch deep in the top of each cookie.
Fill each hole with strawberry jam.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven until browned on bottom.
(Cookies may slide on cookie sheet during baking, but this will not affect their shape.)
Store in tightly covered tin box.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients for dressing.
Add to other ingredients and let stand overnight.

title: bean sprouts
directions: Put seeds in 1-quart jar.
Cover with cheesecloth and jar ring.
Cover with 2 cups water and soak 8 hours.
Drain water from jar.
Fill with fresh water and drain once again.
Sit jar on side on counter, away from direct sunlight.
Repeat rinsing and draining 2 to 3 times a day for 2 to 5 days until sprouts are 1/4-inch long.
When ready to harvest, place jar in sun for several hours to increase chlorophyll.
Rinse and drain well.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, mix sweetened milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mix into glass serving bowl.
Top with wafers and bananas and then add more pudding.
Repeat until all is used, then chill.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Cook and crumble meat.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder; season to taste.
Drain off fat.
Then return meat to pan and add sauce.
Boil noodles.
Mix cheeses together.
In an ungreased pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inch, cover bottom with a layer of noodles, meat, then layer of cheese.
Repeat layering one more time.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese melts and is lightly browned.

title: hungarian stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage; place in enough boiling salted water to cover. With fork in one hand and knife in the other, keep cutting off leaves as they become wilted; drain.
Trim thick center vein of each cabbage leaf.
Brown onion in shortening; add meat, seasonings and rice.
Mix well.
Place tablespoon (or more) of filling on each cabbage leaf and roll, place in pan and cover 2/3 full with water. Arrange sauerkraut on top; and tomato juice.
Cover and cook slowly about 1 1/2 hours, or until rice is tender.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Bake and cool pie shell.
Combine ice cream, pumpkin, honey, spices, and salt.
Blend well and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Freeze until serving time.
To serve garnish with whipped cream and pecan halves.

title: two easy butterscotch pies
directions: Heat brown sugar and water to boiling point. Pour over sifted flour, cornstarch and white sugar.
Cook until thick. Add slightly beaten egg yolks and cook one minute longer.

title: raised pancakes
directions: Put in large mixing bowl the lukewarm water and yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add lukewarm milk and Wesson oil.
Combine salt and sugar to flour and add to yeast mixture; beat well.
Put in large, covered, bowl and let stand overnight out of refrigerator. When time to cook waffles, add eggs and soda, beating well.
Cook on hot waffle iron or hot griddle.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature and mix all ingredients well.
Roll into ball and roll into chopped pecans.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Sift together cocoa, cake flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with milk, then add boiling water, vinegar and vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: poached orange roughy
directions: Rinse fish and pat dry.
Cook celery and onion in oil until tender.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Cover fish with tomato and lemon slices.
Combine water, sugar, vinegar, wine and bay leaf.
Pour over fish mixture.
Cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: layered salad
directions: Place lettuce in clear bowl.
Sprinkle next 3 ingredients in layers.
Break peas apart while frozen and sprinkle on top. Spread mayo on top like icing and sprinkle with sugar.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add layers of bacon, sliced eggs and tomatoes and sprinkle with grated cheeses.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Broil
7 to 10 minutes on each side.
Eat as
is
or
use
with your favorite sauces. Makes 32 (1-inch) balls or 16 (2-inch) balls.

title: chocolate chip cookies (3)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients & mix well.
(May refrigerate overnight.)
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water. Add the scalded milk to the sugar, salt and shortening. Cool to lukewarm. Add 1 cup flour. Beat. Add yeast and egg. Mix well. Add enough flour to make soft dough. Knead 10 minutes. Put in greased bowl and let rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours. Punch down and let set. Shape and place in greased pan. Let rise again, about 45 to 50 minutes. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together in bowl.
Add sugar, brown sugar, egg, butter and vanilla; blend well.
Melt 1/3 cup chocolate chips in top of double boiler over hot water.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Add melted chocolate to flour mixture.
Stir in nuts and remaining chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Drain fat.
Add soup and mixed vegetables.
Mix with meat.
Pour into casserole dish. Spread mashed potatoes over top of mixture.
Also add cheese the last few minutes in oven.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: leroy cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix oleo, cake mix and egg.
Press into pan.
Pour over this, mixture of cream cheese, 2 eggs, confectioners sugar and chopped pecans.
Bake until golden brown. Bake glass pan at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes and metal pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: festive spoon cake
directions: Cut fruit; combine with water, 3/4 cup sugar, lemon juice and allspice.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Set aside.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together in a bowl and place in a buttered baking dish. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk-coconut cream pie
directions: Cream the butter until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in sugar. Beat in eggs and flour.
Add remaining ingredients. Mixture will be curdled.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Bake about 30 minutes longer or until set.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, food coloring, vinegar and vanilla. Sift flour and soda together and add to sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Pour into prepared cake pans (3 layers or a 13 x 9-inch).
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
May need to bake sheet cake a few minutes longer.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.
Delicious served over chopped or shredded cabbage.
Pour over just before serving.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Combine all ingredients, except lemon juice and apples, in a large kettle.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice.

title: mom's basic barbecue sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan off the heat, mix the brown sugar, cider vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and coffee to dissolve the sugar. Whisk in the ketchup and corn oil.
Bring sauce to a boil and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes to blend flavors; cool.

title: dinosaur stew
directions: Begin about 2 months in advance by cutting dinosaur into small cubes.
Start dinosaur cooking.
Bring to boil and cook for one month.
While meat is cooking, prepare vegetables.
When meat is tender, add vegetables and season to taste.
Simmer for a month.
Serve with hard rolls.
Should serve 5,000 people.
If more is needed, add the rabbits, but only as last resort as most people don't like hare in their stew.

title: trudy's spinach salad with raspberry vinaigrette
directions: Combine all ingredients and add vinaigrette.

title: vanilla wafer nut cake
directions: Mix well.
Put in tube pan and bake 2 hours at 250°.

title: italian style zucchini
directions: Cut ends from zucchini (do not pare); cook in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Halve lengthwise.
Remove pulp with spoon; reserve shells.
Combine zucchini pulp, crumbs, 1/2 cup cheese, onion, parsley, salt, pepper and eggs; mix well.
Fill shells. Dot with butter and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: forget-it-stew
directions: Dump everything together in your cooking pot.
Place ingredients in either a large electric slow cooker on low, covered, for 12 to 14 hours total cooking time.
Or a deep cast-iron Dutch oven with tight lid in very low 250° oven for approximately 6 hours total cooking time.
(The secret to tender meat is very low heat over a long period.)

title: trucker's beef stew
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, simmer beef cubes and potatoes with 4 ounces water for about 15 minutes, or until tender.
Drain water.
Add carrots, celery, peppers, onion, ketchup, steak sauce and 2 ounces water and combine thoroughly.
Cover pan and simmer over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Serve with brown rice.
All ingredients can be put in a crock-pot and cooked on low for six to eight hours.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° until done.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add rice, onion and green pepper. Cook and stir over high heat until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, water and salt.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Hull berries and set aside.
Combine pie filling mix, sour cream and Cool Whip in bowl.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, about 1 minute.
Spoon half the filling into crust. Arrange strawberries (stem down) in filling.
Top with remaining filling.
Chill in refrigerator 3 hours.

title: apple butter
directions: Make pulp by cooking apples and running through strainer or Foley mill.
Mix all ingredients and cook until it thickens or desired consistency.
Put in hot jars leaving 1 inch at top. Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Test the seals.
I make this in the crock-pot.
Less danger of sticking and much easier.

title: double layered pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in
Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into a bowl.
Add pudding mix; beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 or 2 minutes.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Garnish with Cool Whip or nuts, if desired.
Spices can be substituted with McCormick pumpkin pie spice.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over the top.
Melt margarine and pour evenly over the top of the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: peanutty ice cream pie
directions: Lightly grease a 9-inch pie plate.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine ground peanuts, margarine or butter and sugar.
Press mixture firmly onto bottom and up sides of pie plate.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.

title: cherry cheese tart(yields 12 to 16 servings)
directions: Using 8 or 9-inch layer cake pans, make and cool cake as on package.
Soften cream cheese.
Add sugar, nutmeg and milk.
Beat until smooth.

title: lima-broccoli bake
directions: Cook first 2 ingredients until almost done; drain.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Add vegetables and stir well.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Brown 2 cups Rice Krispies in 1 stick oleo.
Put over top.
Loosely cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: brian's gunsmoken club turkey
directions: Toast two pieces of wheat bread in toaster to your fixen. Spray some pam on your frying pan and turn on low to medium heat. Place turkey bacon in pan and fry until crisp.
Place shredded turkey on one piece of toast to your fixen.
Put three slices onion on turkey, 1 slice tomato on onions, 3 pieces sliced roman lettuce on top of tomato.
Add plenty of honey mustard on the other piece of toast to your fixen and place 2-3 slices of turkey bacon on top of your goodies then smash you piece of toast loaded with honey mustard on top.
Cut with a knife like a triangle.
What a Sandwich!
Consume and make another one.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cocoa. Stir in milk, melted shortening and pecans.
Spreads in 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and cocoa.
Pour 1 3/4 cups hot water over entire batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zesty creamy dressing dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour and serve.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients except crumbs.
Alternate layers of macaroni and other ingredients.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake 1 hour in moderate 375° oven in 2-quart casserole.
Garnish with peppers, olives, etc.

title: pumpkin jazz
directions: Mix the ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan. Sprinkle on top one box yellow cake mix.
Dribble 1 1/2 sticks melted margarine on top of cake mix.
Top with 3/4 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Bring blueberries, water, 3/4 cup sugar and lemon peel to a boil in a medium saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves. Reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into a greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, beat margarine and remaining 3/4 cup sugar with electric mixer until fluffy. Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture. Spoon drops of batter over blueberries.
Bake in preheated 375° oven about 30 minutes or until bubbly and top is brown. Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oxtail soup
directions: Cut the oxtails in small pieces (about 1 inch long).
Wash, drain and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dredge with flour and brown in fat or bacon drippings in a pan on top of stove.
Add to the stock carrots and onions and simmer until the meat is tender. If desired, the soup may be thickened with flour batter.
Just before serving, add sufficient stock to make 5 gallons of soup.

title: baked potato topper
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat until onions are cooked (transparent).
Spoon over potatoes.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Pare, core and quarter apples, then half each quarter crosswise to make chunks (about 7 cups).
Place in large bowl.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, cool.
Mix half with half the fruit.
Spread in long dish.
Harden in refrigerator (or more quickly in freezer).
Spread sour cream on top, then other half of jello and fruit mixture.
Harden.

title: easter cupcakes
directions: Make cupcakes and put the frosting on.
Put the coconut in a bag.
Add a little food coloring and shake.
Keep adding until the coconut looks like grass.
Sprinkle coconut on frosted cupcake. Decorate with jelly beans on top; cut licorice 4 inches long.
Put one end on left side and put other end on right side to make a handle.

title: bonnie's special meat loaf
directions: Pour on the loaf and bake for 20 minutes longer.

title: suttle chili
directions: Brown turkey, onion, garlic and drain drippings.
Add water and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Uncover, simmer 1 hour.
Stir from time to time.
Discard bay leaf.
Yield 10 1/2 cups.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice for seven minutes.
Add margarine and milk.
Cook slow for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until thickened.
Pour into dish and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Beat in the egg, then the vanilla and orange rind.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Refrigerate.
Roll and cut into shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheets 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
These can be decorated before baking or frosted and trimmed when cool.

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Mix chicken with spaghetti sauce in a large bowl.
Beat egg with Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and pepper in another bowl.
Layer uncooked noodles, egg mixture, Mozzarella cheese and chicken mixture, 1/2 at a time in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: sausage casserole
directions: While cooking sausage, add pepper and onion and cook together. Cook macaroni and drain.
Pour into casserole dish; top with cheese slices.
Drain sausage; add milk, flour, water and mushroom soup.
Bring to a boil, then pour over macaroni.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and stir until syrupy. Add whipped topping and angel food cake.
Chill until firm.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters and toss in 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Put into ungreased Bundt or tube pan.
Bring 1 stick of margarine and 1 cup sugar to a boil and pour over and around biscuits in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and turn upside down onto a plate.

title: potato candy
directions: Cook potato; mash. Add powdered sugar until thick enough to roll out (like pie crust). Spread with peanut butter. Roll up, jellyroll-style; refrigerate.
When cold, slice into thin slices and serve.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Oil pan; sprinkle coconut on bottom of pan and nuts.
Pour cake batter on top of this.
Melt cream cheese, margarine and sugar together on top of stove.
Stir constantly until dissolved together and pour this on top of cake batter.
Bake for 30 or 35 minutes or until done at 350°.
Makes 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan or 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: pork and gravy
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan with butter.
Place chops in casserole dish.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chops.
Mix together milk and soup.
Pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook the pasta noodles until almost done (you'll want them a little firm for stirring).
Then use cold water to rinse and let them sit in the refrigerator while doing rest of cutting and chopping of other ingredients.

title: 1-2-3 pound cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cream sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and milk, alternating a little of each.
Beat egg whites.
Fold into batter.
Pour into tube pan. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: chili 'n cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring at one minute intervals.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: potato dish casserole
directions: Line ovenproof casserole dish with potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, uncovered, until potatoes are browned.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef; add broccoli, soup thinned with the milk, 1/2 of the shredded cheese and 1/2 can of fried onions. Heat through.
When potatoes are done, remove from oven and lower temperature to 350°.
Fill with meat and vegetable mixture; cover and put back in oven.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Five minutes before done, remove lid; sprinkle on rest of cheese and onions and cook remaining 5 minutes uncovered.
Enjoy!

title: wicked stepmother's vegie bars
directions: Spread out crescent rolls on cooking sheet (don't separate). Bake and cool.
Mix the cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise and dressing mix together; set aside while rolls bake.
After crescent roll crust is cool, spread cream cheese mixture on top.
Sprinkle vegies and cheese on top, then press in.
Cut in small squares or triangles; serve as appetizers.
You can make this a day ahead of time, and it is so good!

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Saute chicken in olive oil, being sure to add garlic and oregano to oil first.
When chicken is brown, add onion, pepper, mushrooms, wine and tomatoes.
Turn to low and allow to simmer in covered skillet until done.

title: mexican rice(arroz rojo)
directions: Saute rice, onions and garlic until rice changes color (turns whiter and begins to toast).
Add tomato sauce; stir until rice is coated.
Add 2 cups water/broth.
Let simmer until water is almost evaporated, then add last 1/2 cup of water/broth.
Simmer until evaporated.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: * Adjust this up or down to regular hotness desired.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Cook beef and onion until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in taco mix (dry).
Spread in pie plate; sprinkle with chilies.
Beat milk, eggs and baking mix 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute with hand mixer.
Pour over chilies.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomato and cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with shredded lettuce and taco sauce.

title: good morning muffins
directions: In a medium-sized bowl, combine milk and bran.
Set aside 10 minutes; beat in egg, molasses and margarine.
Sift flour and baking soda and add to bran mixture, stirring until moist.
Fill greased muffin tins three-fourths full.
Put in a 400° oven and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and cheese.
Stir in pineapple with juice.
Pour in baking dish.
Mix oleo and crackers; sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: icebox pie
directions: Put mixing bowl and beaters in fridge or freezer.
Dissolve lemon jello in the water.
Add sugar, juice and rind of lemon. Beat Milnot until thick.
Add mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan with graham cracker crust.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together
and pour into 2 small, unbaked pie
shells.
Bake	at 250° for 10 to 15 minutes, then at 325° until top is brown.

title: dried beef gravy
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt the butter and stir in the flour to make a roux.
Whisk in the hot milk, stirring all the time until the mixture thickens.
When the mixture is thick, add the remaining ingredients and heat for a moment.
Yields 4 servings.

title: quiche
directions: Combine eggs, sour cream and milk.
Add filling.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and warm water and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients. Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Blend thoroughly with spoon.
Refrigerate or make into rolls.
When needed, make rolls and let rise at room temperature for 1 hour. Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: rice krispies treat
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a large bowl.
Melt Almond Bark as directed on pour over mixture.
Mix all ingredients and spoon onto wax paper to cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Boil, debone and chop chicken in bite size pieces. Chop onion and bell pepper. Mix with chicken. Layer casserole with tortillas, dipped in hot chicken broth. As you layer this, sprinkle with garlic powder, chili powder, cheese, hot pepper sauce, tomatoes and green chilies. Mix soups together (you may add a wee bit of the broth if you wish). Layer this also with other ingredients. Be sure to save enough of the cheese to sprinkle on top layer. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned rice pudding
directions: Add rice, milk, sugar, butter and salt to a heavy 3-quart saucepan over medium heat until tiny bubbles form around edge of pan, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until rice is very tender.

title: baked spaghetti casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in casserole.
Make 3 layers.
Put on top 1 can whole tomatoes and lots of Parmesan cheese.
In 350° oven, bake 45 minutes.
Serve with salad and French bread.
Serves 8.

title: cheese cake
directions: Freeze milk until crystals form.
Chill bowl and beaters. Dissolve gelatin in hot water and set aside to cool.
Crush graham crackers and mix with margarine.
Spread 2/3 of mixture in bottom of 11 x 7-inch pan.
Cream cheese and sugar.
Add cooled gelatin and lemon juice.
Whip milk until stiff.
Fold into creamed mixture.
Pour into crust-lined pan and sprinkle with remaining cracker mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Making a batter of butter, sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Heat cherries and 3/4 cup sugar until sugar is dissolved. Pour batter into utility dish.
Pour cherries on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: stay fluffy meringue
directions: Let egg whites reach room temperature.
Cook cornstarch and 2 tablespoons sugar and water until clear and thick; let cool.
Beat whites and sugar until foamy, then add to cornstarch mixture and beat until stiff.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8 baking dish.
Layer items as listed, starting with graham cracker crumbs and ending with sweetened condensed milk.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 10 more minutes.
Top should be lightly browned. Slide knife around edges of dish before completely cooled.
Once cooled, cut into 1-inch squares.

title: creole peanut and tomato soup
directions: Combine soup, milk and peanut butter in a medium saucepan and warm over medium heat.
Stir until peanut butter melts.
Add Tabasco sauce to taste.
Serve hot.

title: punch
directions: Mix 1 quart of water with Kool-Aid in a 1 gallon jug.
Add juices to Kool-Aid mixture.
Set aside.
Mix 2 cups sugar and 2 cups water; heat on low until sugar is dissolved.
Cool and then pour into other mixture.
Put in freezer until slushy, then serve.

title: beef rice
directions: Mix together in a greased baking dish the rice, minced onion and beef consomme.
Cut up butter and place on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together in order given. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Cut thin slice from top of each potato.
Carefully remove pulp.
Put pulp into mixing bowl; mash and set aside.
Keep potato shell warm.
Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Defrost green beans.
Add defrosted green beans, milk and soy sauce to margarine.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly.
Stir in sour cream, potatoes, meat and chestnuts.
Heat thoroughly, stirring lightly. Heap potato mixture into shells and garnish with paprika.

title: spritz cookies
directions: You also need decorator beads.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Dip chicken in sauce. Place in foil lined pan.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
This makes sauce for 1 chicken.
Double for 2 or 3 chickens.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, seasoning and 1 cup water; simmer on low. In separate pot, melt Velveeta and Ro-Tel tomatoes. In casserole dish, layer meat, rice and cheese mixture and top with Doritos. Don't allow casserole to sit too long before eating because the Doritos will become soggy.

title: squash pie
directions: Melt butter; add drained squash.
Let cool.
Combine sugar and beaten eggs; add cooled squash, flour, vanilla and baking powder. Put in greased pan (6 x 8-inch) and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot as a vegetable or cool as a dessert.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cabbage-beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef in large saucepan or Dutch oven, breaking it into dime size pieces as it cooks.
When meat is brown, place in a colander and drain off all grease.
Rinse the saucepan with water. Return meat to pan and add all ingredients except cabbage.
Stir to mix well, then add cabbage.
Bring to a rolling boil; reduce heat and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: banana-graham cracker cake
directions: Place the graham crackers on platter or large plate. Slice bananas lengthwise (1/4 to 1/2 thick) and place on top of crackers. Top bananas with another layer of crackers. Continue until you have 5 layers. Frost with Boiled Icing (follows). Let set overnight. Graham crackers will absorb moisture from bananas. Texture will be cake-like, very moist.

title: black bean burritos
directions: Fry onion, green pepper and garlic until soft.
Mix in beans (undrained) along with chicken and 1 cup of salsa, cumin and salt. Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread filling across the middle of each tortilla and sprinkle with about 2 tablespoons cheese.
Roll up and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread remaining salsa over top and add remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese melts and burritos are heated through.
Serve with sour cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given, in large mixing bowl.
Bake 12 minutes at 325°.
Let set 1 or 2 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes a 30-pound lard can full of cookies.

title: lemonade torte
directions: Blend well, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over crust. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs, then refrigerate.

title: turkey
directions: You will need one large baking bag.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: Mix and form loaf.
Push away from sides of pan or casserole dish.
Pour tomato catsup or tomato juice around or on top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate shake for two
directions: Put in blender.
Turn on blender for 10 seconds and pour into 2 tall glasses.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend or mix thoroughly (except vegetables).
Best if it sets in refrigerator overnight.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook beef; drain grease.
Add onion, pepper and Ro-Tel.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and chili pepper to taste.
Put in 9 x 13 greased pan.
Layer rice, meat and cheese until mixture is gone.
Bake at 375° until cheese is bubbly.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: In large black iron pot, melt butter and add ground chuck. Cook with onions, celery and bell pepper until all are done.
Add mushroom soup, oysters and juice, parsley and corn bread (crumbled into very small pieces).
Add jar of mushrooms before pouring into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add crushed wafers, coconut and pecans. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 275°.
Cook in Bundt pan.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, chocolate chips, and peanut butter together.
Put rice chex into a large bowl. Pour mixture over Chex and mix well. Put powdered sugar into a large paper sack. Add mixture and shake well.

title: crust for pie
directions: Put 1/2 cup oil in bowl.
Pour 1/4 cup milk onto oil; do not stir.
Pour both onto flour.
Stir with fork.
Divide in half and put between wax paper.
Roll out from center.
Do same with second half.

title: candied walnuts
directions: Toast walnuts in a 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Mix other ingredients and stir well.
Place lid on pan and cook until syrup reaches a boil.
Remove lid and simmer until it reaches a soft ball stage.
Put in nuts; stir until all are coated and spread on waxed paper.
Separate before cooling.

title: stuffed bell peppers on rice
directions: Cut tops off pepper, remove seeds and membrane.
Cook peppers in boiling salted water, about 5 minutes; drain.
Soak bread in water or milk to soften, squeeze dry.
Combine bread with meat and next 7 ingredients.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Place in large baking dish.
In sauce pan combine tomatoes, onion, 1 tsp. salt, sugar, cinnamon and cloves; simmer 10 minutes.
Sieve or puree tomato sauce in blender, return to saucepan.
Mix flour with water, add to strained sauce, cook stirring until slightly thickened; pour over peppers.
Cover, bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover; bake 15 minutes more.
Serve on fluffy rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet ricotta cheese pie
directions: Blend everything together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.
Good luck.

title: tadies
directions: Make it with bread, put it on brownies or something.
You're supposed to put ice cream on it.
That's all you do to a brownie.

title: low-fat pimento cheese
directions: Cut cheese into small chunks.
Place all ingredients in food processor.
Add pimento liquid as needed for desired consistency.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a 1 or 1 1/2-quart saucepan, place 2 tablespoons oil and 2 garlic cloves (cut in half).
Apply heat and brown garlic, then remove.
Add 1 1/2 cups rice and brown slightly.
Add water, salsa and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boiling point; stir contents. Cover pot; turn heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes.
(Do not uncover during 20 minutes.)

title: fish batter
directions: Mix ingredients and dip fish in and place in hot oil to fry.

title: overnight salad
directions: Cook the eggs, flour, sugar and juice.
Stir continuously until thick.
Add the cream cheese and marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Add the pineapple and oranges.
When cooled, fold in the Cool Whip.
Put in a dish and chill overnight.

title: sesame chicken drumsticks
directions: In a skillet combine all ingredients except chicken, bring to a boil, cook about 1 to 2 minutes.
Put in the chicken and marinade in cold place for about 2 hours.
Place the chicken in an aluminum foil lined glass baking dish and baste them with marinade during baking every 10 to 15 minutes.
When done, remove chicken from baking dish.
Pour sauce from chicken together with leftover of marinade in a pan and cook the sauce until only half remains. Stir constantly while cooking.
When done pour sauce over chicken. Serve with rice or over mashed potatoes.

title: montana monster cookies
directions: Cream first 7 ingredients.
Then add oatmeal, soda, chips and candies.
Mix well.
Drop by large tablespoons onto cookie sheet and flatten.
Place about 6 to a sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter over medium heat, stirring occasionally until onions are tender and just begin to brown.
Sprinkle with flour.
Gradually stir in 1 can broth.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in remaining broth, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Place 1 slice toast in oven-proof bowl.
Pour soup over toast, sprinkle with cheese.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat until cheese melts and is lightly brown.

title: valerie's hot cheese and artichoke hearts
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and put into a baking dish. Sprinkle top heavily with paprika and additional oregano.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together powdered sugar, peanut butter and butter until well combined.
May need to add additional powder sugar if mixture is very sticky.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening until shortening is pea sized. In measuring cup, mix egg,
vinegar and water.
Add to flour mixture.
This rolls out 3 large crusts.
Bake in a 350° oven until light tan.
This dough freezes well.
A ball in a Ziploc bag in the freezer thawed, rolls and cooks fast.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Butter first.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over butter.
Then pour peaches over other stuff.

title: waverly taffy bars
directions: Line cookie sheet sprayed with Pam with Waverly wafers, close but not overlapping. Sprinkle chopped pecans over wafers.
Cook butter, margarine and sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over wafers. Bake exactly 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly.
Take out immediately and break into pieces.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw the potatoes and mix with onion and oleo.
Mix the mushroom soup and water together.
Add all the ingredients to the potato mixture.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Mix corn flakes with melted oleo and sprinkle over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: french chewing
directions: Mix sugar, cream and Karo in a large, heavy pan.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup very warm water. Add to mixture.
Add paraffin.
Cook to hard ball stage.
Cool in greased pan.
When cool enough, pull (as in taffy) with greased hands until color changes.
When color changes, lay on waxed paper.
Crack with a knife handle into desired sizes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle
apples
with
lemon juice.
Add to apples and toss celery;
cover
and chill.
Just before serving add nuts and raisins.
Add and toss lightly mayonnaise.
Place lightly on crisp lettuce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Add chopped onion and saute until clear.
Add broccoli.
Stir thoroughly.
Add mushroom soup.
Stir and simmer several minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz; mix and simmer a few more minutes.
Add rice; stir and simmer.
If too thick, add small amount of water.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate bits cookies(the best chocolate chip cookie ever!)
directions: Cream shortening until creamy.
Gradually add the sugars and blend well.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and salt.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add alternately with the flour mixture.
Add vanilla and fold in chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoonful on an oiled cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove and cool. Yield: 8 dozen.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix margarine, flour and powdered sugar like pie crust.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken savannah
directions: Melt butter in casserole. Add soup and barbecue sauce. Place chicken in casserole, turning several times to coat. Cover and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: gayle ann's almond burgers
directions: Combine rice and almond meal.
In a blender, mix soy sauce, egg, onion and cheese.
Pour this over rice and almond meal.
Mix thoroughly with the fingers until an even consistency is reached. If desired, add 1/4 cup minced parsley.
Mix, then shape the mixture into burgers and fry them in a tiny bit of oil, preferably on a griddle.
They cook fairly rapidly and brown nicely.
Cook over medium heat until browned, about 5 minutes on each side. Serve on whole wheat buns with lettuce, tomato, sprouts and raw sweet onion rings.
Makes 6 burgers.

title: buttered sourdough bread or rolls
directions: Slice bread.
Combine butter, garlic and basil.
Pour over bread.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Salt and flour chicken; cook in oil until done and keep warm. Bring to a boil the pineapple juice, honey, teriyaki sauce, pepper and chives.
Add sliced pineapple; pour over warm chicken.
Serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Separate eggs.
Put egg whites in a large bowl.
In a casserole dish, mix all the above ingredients except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 7 salad
directions: Mix and serve.
Chill if time allows.

title: my salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together, add vinegar and water.
Cook slow until thick.

title: illinois bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, onion, pepper and seasonings well.
Add beans.
Mix all together and let stand overnight.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream white sugar, brown sugar and shortening in a large mixing bowl. Add eggs and vanilla. Stir until creamy. Add flour, salt and soda. Stir until mixed. Stir in oatmeal. After oatmeal is mixed in, add chocolate chips.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish, then top with the crackers, mixed with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bakes
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, butter and milk to a boil and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar; add eggs, extract, salt, baking powder, and 2 1/2 c. flour. Mix well. Mix raisins, pecans, and remaining 1/2 c. flour; add to batter. Stir just until blended. Pour into lined and buttered tube pan. Place foil over top of cake and bake at 275° for about 2 hours. Place pan of water in oven under cake while it is baking.

title: cherry goop
directions: Beat together Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Add pineapple (drained), cherry pie filling, nuts and coconut.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: indian pudding
directions: Scald the milk.
Add butter.
Gradually beat in the corn meal. Stir until slightly thickened.
Remove from stove.
Add other ingredients, beating well.
Pour into a well buttered casserole. Bake in a 275° to 300° oven for 2 hours.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: aunt nannie's wonderful walnut broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Spoon broccoli into prepared 2-quart casserole.

title: david's bumpy pudding
directions: Soak tapioca in water overnight or a couple of hours.
In saucepan beat eggs.
Add sugar and continue beating until blended. Add milk.
Stir and add tapioca and water.
Stir.
Cook until it thickens, stirring constantly. Boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and almond or 1/2 teaspoon almond and 1/2 teaspoon lemon extract.
Cool and serve.
Serves 6 people or 2 servings for David.

title: cream cheese dessert
directions: Roll out 1 can of rolls on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; pinch seams together.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar vanilla and egg yolk.
Spread on pastry.
Roll out second can of biscuits on top of cheese mixture.
Pinch seams together.
Brush on egg white.
Bake 350° for 20-30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: escalloped smoked sausage and potatoes
directions: Combine cheese, sour cream, parsley and onion.
Add potatoes and sausage; turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine in a pan and mix with peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies and mix.
Add sugar.
Mix and shape into balls.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours or longer.
Melt 2 small Hershey bars, 12 ounces chocolate chips and 1/2 stick paraffin.
Dip balls and set on wax paper.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Set oven to "broil."
Place shrimp in individual serving dishes or one large serving dish in single layer.
In 1-quart saucepan, add garlic powder, butter, lemon juice, salt, oregano and pepper.
Heat over low heat until butter is melted, add parsley and stir.
Pour mixture over shrimp and broil 5 to 8 minutes until shrimp are pink.

title: cocoa meringue pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan.
Add milk slowly, stirring well.
Cook and stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil and is thickened.
Stir in egg yolks, one at a time.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 3 minutes or longer. Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly, then pour into a baked pie shell.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, salt and water.
Stir flour, sugar and butter with a fork.
Put over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crisp. Serve warm with cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In long Pyrex dish, put in layers asparagus, eggs and olives. Make a white sauce of the butter, flour and milk; add cheese if desired.
Cover asparagus mixture with white sauce and put buttered toast crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 or 40 minutes until brown.

title: quick and easy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine ingredients.
Shape into loaf. Place in baking pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: alan's sauce(sauce for grilled burgers)
directions: Salt and pepper burgers heavily before grilling. Mix sauces as directed. Brush on hamburger patties while grilling.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Choose small, bite-size mushrooms for this dish.
Combine the first 6 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Heat gently until the sugar dissolves.
Add the mushrooms and continue to heat for about 5 minutes, but do not boil.
A small sliced onion could also be added at this point.
Let the mixture cool; add the sprig of oregano, then refrigerate for at least a day to let the flavor marry.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: butterscotch cream pie
directions: Blend flour, cornstarch and salt together in a small bowl. Mix well with a fork.
Cream brown sugar, butter and eggs together in another medium-sized bowl.
Add the flour mixture to this second bowl of ingredients.
Mix well.
Slowly pour the scalding milk into this mixture and beat well.

title: greek spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Brown (not burn) butter with minced garlic. Sprinkle layer of Parmesan cheese on large platter.
Put 1/2 of spaghetti on top of cheese layer.
Sprinkle another layer of cheese over spaghetti.
Put remaining spaghetti on top.
Sprinkle with more cheese.
Spoon hot browned butter on top.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: almond stuffed dates
directions: Stuff each date with an almond.
Cut the bacon strips into thirds.
Wrap bacon around each date.
Secure with toothpick. Place on foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until bacon is crisp.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Peel banana and place in a blender.
Add milk, honey and ice. Turn blender on and whip.

title: classic lasagna
directions: In large heavy pan, lightly brown beef and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes.
(Put through blender or cut up), paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic, pepper and oregano; simmer uncovered about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook lasagna as directed; drain.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread 1 cup sauce.
Alternate layers of lasagna, sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Allow to stand 15 minutes to set up; cut in squares to serve.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a mixing bowl; mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 2 1/2 tablespoons melted butter and nuts in a small mixing bowl; mix well.
Sprinkle topping over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: company green beans
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add 2/3 cup of cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked fruit compote
directions: Drain all fruit, reserving 1/2 cup apricot juice.
Pour fruit into casserole dish.
Lay 2 large fresh strawberries on top. Sprinkle 1 cup brown sugar on top of fruit.
Mix 1/2 cup apricot juice with 1/2 cup rum and pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve warm.
(You may mix ingredients together the night before and bake the following day.)

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion in small amount of butter.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 225° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring about every 20 minutes.

title: spinach pie
directions: Open filo dough; cut in half.
With one half, start layering the bottom of a 12 x 9-inch glass pan, brushing each layer with melted margarine.
When half is done, mix the cottage cheese, drained, chopped spinach, beaten eggs, Feta cheese and bread crumbs well.
Spread this filling over the bottom filo layer. Repeat with second half, brushing each layer with margarine.
Cut into squares before cooking.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix.
Put in two 9 x 13 pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Stir occasionally, press in pans, cool.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix butter, cornstarch, lemon juice, sugar and eggs altogether and bring to a boil.
Refrigerate and chill.
Layer bananas, dressing and Cool Whip.
Repeat.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box and pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt butter and mix with softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spoon over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let set a few minutes and then turn upside-down on a platter.

title: hot crab dip
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients over low heat and stir until cream cheese has melted and mixture is heated through. Serve warm with Ritz crackers.
Yields 4 cups.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and freeze.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet, draining off most of fat.
Add onion and green peppers to bacon fat.
Cook over medium heat until onion is yellow.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Cook uncovered over low heat about 15 minutes.
Add 1 small can drained tiny peas.
Good with pork chops.

title: fried rice and chicken
directions: Beat eggs and cook in a frypan without stirring. When set, remove from pan and cut into strips.
Set aside.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut stems off mushrooms and finely chop.
Clean out caps of mushrooms.
Mix grated cheese, stems, spices or seasonings of your choice.
Put into caps.
Place on cookie sheet or in casserole dish; bake until cheese is melted and slightly browned.

title: special scalloped potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and slice potatoes.
Mix soup, milk and garlic. Pour over potato slices thoroughly.
Bake in covered casserole dish in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until fork inserts easily into potatoes.
During the last half hour of baking, spread cheese over the top (be sure to keep covered).

title: heavenly ice cream pie
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin.
Stir to dissolve, then add ice milk and lemon juice.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Toss together and pack lightly into loaf pan.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: caramel apples
directions: Cook pineapple, flour, sugar and cider vinegar until thickened; cool.
Combine apples, peanuts and Cool Whip; mix with pineapple mixture in large bowl.
Add a few crushed peanuts on top.

title: stewed okra and tomatoes
directions: Put in pot; cover and cook 30 to 40 minutes.
May need to add some water.
Yields 6 servings.
Good with green beans and corn bread.

title: spicy applesauce dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add cold water.
Measure 1 cup of jello and add applesauce and cinnamon.
Spoon into dessert glasses; chill for 30 minutes.
Chill remaining jello until slightly thickened.
Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package.
Fold in thickened jello, blending well.
Spoon over applesauce mixture in glasses.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then add eggs, vanilla and melted shortening.
Mix and roll out on counter with a little flour sprinkled on top.
Cut out and bake at 350°.

title: hot mocha mix
directions: Combine and mix well in blender.
Store in airtight container. For one serving, mix 2 tablespoons mix in 1 cup boiling water.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine soup, milk and pepper. Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until mixture begins to bubble.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In skillet, heat butter and saute onion, celery and rice until rice is golden brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat and let stand 10 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine all ingredients, except beets, in a large saucepan. Simmer 15 minutes.
Pack beets into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch head room.
Remove cinnamon.
Bring pickling liquid to a boil. Pour hot liquid over beets.
Leave 1/4-inch head room.
Remove air bubbles.
Adjust caps.
Process pints and quarts 30 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields 6 pints.

title: peanut butter krispies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup; bring to a boil and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and Cocoa Krispies; drop on wax paper.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the sugar and eggs.
Add the pumpkin, oil and water; mix.
Add the flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: baked onion soup
directions: Add oil and butter and heat.
Add sliced onions and cook, covered, until almost tender.
Uncover and brown lightly.
Take off heat and add the flour (mix).
Let sit for 3 minutes.
Return to heat and add the beef broth; cook slowly for 1/2 hour.
Add scalded milk and remove from heat and stir.

title: garden pasta salad(main dish)
directions: Combine salad dressing, parsley, basil and garlic; mix well. Add cheese, broccoli and noodles; mix lightly.
Chill.
Arrange tomatoes on platter; top with pasta salad.
Makes 6 servings, 363 calories per serving.
Preparation time: 20 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Saute onion and pepper in 3 tablespoons of butter. Mix together soup and milk.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly in large bowl.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.
(Can freeze after mixing all ingredients together and baking.)

title: "uncle arzo" salad(also known as "frog-eye salad")
directions: Prepare orzo according to package directions.
Add fruits and prepared jello.
Let cool before stirring in whipped topping. Refrigerate 2 or more hours before serving.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Rinse and cook wild rice.
Brown hamburger; add carrots, celery and onion; saute.
Add mushrooms and 1 1/2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Simmer together until carrots are almost tender.
Add rice and add diluted mushroom soup.
Bring to a boil; add salt and pepper to taste and a dash of soy sauce as desired.
Pour in casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Chinese noodles may be added for topping.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix together shortening and sugar.
Add tomato soup.
Add baking soda, dissolved in warm water.
Add spices and flour.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: foolproof roast beef
directions: Must be standing rib roast.
Will
not work with rolled rib roast.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Mix all. Pour in unbaked pie crust. Top with 1/2 cup coconut. Bake at 350° until set and lightly browned.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: In shallow dish, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Roll chicken in flour mixture and brown.
Remove from skillet.
In same skillet, mix the butter, cranberries, water, brown sugar, nutmeg and vinegar (optional).
Cook and stir until cranberries burst. Then pour over chicken and bake in oven for 45 minutes.
Baste once or twice.

title: taco pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie pan or square baking pan.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown and drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in pan and top with chilies.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth (1 minute with mixer).
Pour over all ingredients.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with sliced tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream, if desired.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat milk, butter and chocolate until mixture boils.
Remove from heat. Add confectioners sugar and vanilla. Beat until smooth and creamy. If too thin, let cool slightly.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Alternate layers of green beans and onion rings in a casserole.
Mix 1/4 cup juice from beans with mushroom soup and pour over bean and onion mixture.
Add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to bean mixture.
Stir this into the creamed mixture. Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut bananas and drain the canned fruit, saving the juice from the apricots.
Combine all fruit.
Mix the pudding with the apricot juice and pour over the fruit.
Before mixing fruit, cover bananas with Fruit-Fresh.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Using a 9 x 12-inch pan, tear lettuce in little pieces and fill pan almost 1/2 full.
Add onions and celery.
Add defrosted peas; cover lettuce fully.
Spread mayonnaise (about 1 cup) to cover peas.
Sprinkle sugar on top of mayonnaise.
Cover with shredded cheese; cover completely.
Garnish with bacon on top.

title: cap'n crunch-pretzel candy
directions: Melt almond bark.
Mix well in a large bowl the dry ingredients, then quickly stir in the melted almond bark.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Let stand 20 to 30 minutes.
Store in an airtight container.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash unpeeled potatoes; cut lengthwise into wedges or strips. Place, skin side down, on 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, brushing with oil-cheese mixture every 15 minutes.
Turn potatoes over the last 15 minutes.

title: chicken ritz
directions: Cook chicken until tender and cut into small pieces.
Mix sour cream, soup and chicken together.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Put crushed Ritz crackers on top of chicken mixture.
Cut oleo into small pieces and place around on top of crackers.
Cover and put in microwave for about 10 minutes or bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: apple butter(made in crock pot)
directions: Put the chopped apples in a crock pot.
Sprinkle the sugar and cinnamon over the top. Cover and cook on high for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add vinegar and stir.
Reduce heat to low and continue cooking several hours until apples are the consistency of applesauce.
Any large pieces of apples can be mashed with a potato masher or fork.
Continue cooking to thicken slightly.
Spoon into jars and seal immediately.
Also freezes well.

title: ribbon jello
directions: (Takes some time to assemble, but well worth it for a dramatic and beautiful dessert.)

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald milk and cool to lukewarm.
Crumble yeast in mixing bowl.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar and half the milk and mix well.
Add well beaten eggs.
Cream margarine with remaining sugar and salt and add to first mixture.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Knead well.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk. Place on floured board and let stand 10 minutes.
Roll out and spread with melted butter.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cinnamon and 1/3 cup sugar.
You can add raisins or drained crushed pineapple or nuts.
Roll up like jelly roll and cut in 2-inch slices and place in greased pan, cut side up.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake 20 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Drain crab meat; add all ingredients, season mix last.
Shape in 1-inch patties.
Roll in some of the seasoned mix with a little flour.
Brown on both sides in shallow hot oil.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the hamburg, crackers, onion, salt, pepper, green pepper, 1/2 can tomato soup and eggs together.
Put the rest of the tomato soup in the bottom of casserole.
Put the hamburg mixture and spread a whole can of tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread pecans in pan.
Place frozen rolls as evenly as possible.
(Leave space between them.) Sprinkle with dry pudding.
Melt butter and mix in brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour mixture over rolls.
Cover with damp towel and let stand overnight (about 8 hours).
Do not refrigerate.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately invert pan.
Pig out!

title: mother's tomato preserves
directions: Scald tomatoes and peel; cut into quarters.
Slice lemon; add to tomatoes and sugar.
Cook until mix is thick.

title: easy cream cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare crusts.
In medium saucepan, place 1/2 cup sugar and butter.
Heat until butter is melted, stirring constantly.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and press mixture evenly over the bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: wild duck gumbo
directions: First, skin and debone duck breasts.
Cut into quarters or cubes.
Salt and pepper duck meat to taste.
Next make a roux. Roux consists of ingredients in a cast-iron pot.
Melt 4 tablespoons vegetable shortening and stir in flour until brown. Stir in chopped onions, then put in duck meat and saute for 1 or 2 minutes.
Immediately stir in boiling water.
Add chopped bell peppers and chopped celery and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to a simmer.
Add smoked link sausage, cut into slices.
Cook for 1 hour or more.
Serve over rice and hot cornbread.
Finally, add a dash or two of file for taste.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Bring broth and enough water to boil to cook spaghetti.
Cook 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand until spaghetti absorbs most of the broth.
Mix soups, milk, salt and pepper in saucepan and heat on medium-high until it starts to bubble.
Stir in chicken.
Put spaghetti in large casserole dish and pour soup and chicken mixture on top.
Add grated cheese over top.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs until light.
Gradually add the sugar.
Beat well.
Beat in the cooking oil.
Grate the zucchini. Add the cinnamon, flour, salt, soda, baking powder and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake 2 large loaves at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beer batter fish
directions: Add egg yolks, oil and beer to dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites very stiff; fold into batter.
Dip and fry.

title: nannie kidd's pound cake
directions: Let eggs and oleo get to room temperature. Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add flour a little at a time, but just blend; do not beat. Add flavoring last. Pour into a greased bottom tube pan (do not grease sides). Bake at 300° until straw comes out clean (about 1 hour).

title: pink salad
directions: Mix the first four ingredients.
Fold in the Cool Whip and mix well.
Chill.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and set aside 1/4 cup Jell-O. Mix and congeal the first 4 ingredients.
In an oblong dish, mix Cool Whip with 1/4 cup Jell-O at medium speed.
Combine cheese, sugar and vanilla with Cool Whip mixture and nuts.
Pour over congealed mixture.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim crusts from bread and flatten with rolling pin.
Blend cheeses until smooth.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Spread evenly on each bread slice.
Drain asparagus on paper towels.
Roll one spear in each slice of bread.
Dip in butter to coat evenly or brush butter over roll.
Place on cookie sheet side by side, seam side down.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until brown and crisp.
Cut into thirds and serve hot.
Makes 60.

title: chocolate nut zucchini bread
directions: Grease
and
flour
inch
tube pan or 2 bread pans. Preheat
oven to 350°.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cocoa in large bowl.
Set aside.
In large bowl, beat 4 eggs, 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Gradually add oil and beat it.
Add zucchini and mix altogether.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook broccoli per package directions and drain well.
Mix broccoli with all other ingredients.
Bake in an 8 inch square pan or iron skillet at 400° for 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart saucepan, brown meat in hot oil on all sides. Spoon off fat.
Stir in soups and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low and cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 45 minutes or until vegetables are fork-tender.
Remove roast and vegetables.

title: honey butter
directions: Cream butter well. Add honey and lemon juice. Mix well. Pour into container to mold. Very good with hot biscuits or toast.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan.
Add the chocolate and stir over very low heat until the chocolate is melted.
Then add the boiling water slowly, stirring constantly, and bring to a boil. Add the sugar and corn syrup, stirring until dissolved.
Simmer 5 minutes, then add the vanilla and salt.
Serve hot or warm over ice cream or pudding.
Serves 6.

title: punch
directions: Can be made 2 to 3 days ahead.
Be sure to stir well while making and before serving.
Makes 35 to 40 servings.

title: breakfast burrito(diabetic)
directions: Combine tomato and basil; set aside. In large nonstick skillet over medium heat, saute potato and onion in margarine until tender. Pour Egg Beaters into skillet; sprinkle with pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until set. Divide egg mixture evenly between tortillas. Top with cheese. Fold tortillas over egg mixture. Top with tomato mixture. Makes 4 servings.

title: butter frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add a tiny bit more milk for spreading consistency, if desired.
Makes a great cake decorating frosting.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Melt butter and mix all ingredients except shrimp. Lay shrimp in a shallow pan. Pour sauce over shrimp. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done (test to see). Stir every 5 to 7 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a bowl.
Pour into 2 greased pie plates.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.
No crust needed, makes its own crust.

title: michigan wonders
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, cocoa, salt, butter and milk. Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Put by teaspoons on wax paper covered cookie sheet and freeze.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water 5 to 6 minutes or until tender.
Drain on paper towels.
Pat dry.
Melt butter in saucepan; add ginger, brown sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Add carrots; cook over low heat 3 to 4 minutes, stirring gently.
Makes 4 servings.

title: favorite coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, blending well after each addition.
Blend in flavoring. Spoon batter into 4 or 5 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely and spread coconut icing between layers.

title: ham quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Trim excess pastry around edges; fold edges under and flute.
Prick bottom and sides of pastry with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes; remove from oven and gently prick with fork.
Bake an additional 5 minutes. You may use a premade pastry, following same cooking directions. Combine cheese and flour; sprinkle evenly into pastry shell.
Top with ham.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, half and half, dry mustard and salt, stirring well.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: sweet fried matzos
directions: Soak matzos in water.
Squeeze out well.
Add to beaten eggs. Then add salt, sugar and cinnamon.
Melt butter and add batter. Fry until brown on both sides.
Serves 2.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites until foamy. Beat in sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy. Fold in peanut butter and cereal.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on box using 13X9 inch pan (leave cake in pan after it is done).

While baking, mix condensed milk, cream of coconut and pineapple all together. After cake is done and cooled, poke holes all over the top of cake (use a plastic straw). Pour mixture of pineapple, condensed milk and cream of coconut over top of cake. Spread Cool Whip over top of cake. Garnish with sliced pineapple, cherries and toasted coconut.

title: parmesan-romano chicken bake
directions: Dry the chicken pieces on paper toweling.
Dip each piece into the beaten eggs.

title: corn relish
directions: Peel the onion, leaving a little of the root attached, and cut it lengthwise in half.
Lay each onion half flat on the chopping board and slice horizontally, then vertically toward the root, leaving the slices attached at the root end.
Finally, cut across to make dice.
Peel the strings from the celery stalk with the vegetable peeler.
Cut the celery stalk across into thin slices.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange peel.
Add sugar.
Let stand until sugar is dissolved.
Mix Jell-O and water together.
Let cool.
After cool, mix with cranberry mixture.
Add celery, nutmeats and grapes.
Mix together.
Let chill until firm.

title: slow-cooked string beans and ham
directions: Place the ham bone or piece of ham steak in a heavy saucepan or Dutch oven with water to cover and bring to a boil.
Top and tail the string beans; cut them to 2-inch lengths.
Add the beans to the boiling ham bone along with the remaining ingredients. Lower to a simmer and cook for 1 hour.

title: play dough
directions: Stir together soda and starch in saucepan.
Add water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture consistency is moist like mashed potatoes, turn out on plate and cover with damp cloth.
When cool enough to handle, gently pat until smooth. Store unused portion in tightly sealed plastic bag, but remove to bring to room temperature.

title: mrs. fields' cookies
directions: Mix together 1 cup each of butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add to this mixture the 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat the oats in a blender until they are a powder.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together. Then add chocolate chips, Hershey bar (which has been broken into small chunks) and chopped pecans.
Make into golf ball size balls and place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.

title: walking taco dip-layered
directions: Spread on 12-inch round plate.

title: old-fashioned gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a large loaf pan and bake for about an hour.

title: spiced tea
directions: Put the 3 tea bags into 1 filter basket of a drip coffee maker.
Fill water basket full and brew tea.
Put brewed tea in a 2-gallon pitcher and fill with water.
Add sugar to taste.
Accent with mint sprigs and slices of lemon and orange.

title: sour orange pie
directions: Mix milk and egg yolks and slowly add sour orange juice.
Beat hard.
Beat 1 egg white stiff.
Fold into sour orange mixture. Beat remaining egg whites and gradually add sugar and cream of tartar.
Put into baked pie shell and bake at 350° until egg whites are golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Help yourself to sour oranges anytime.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan and drain off grease.
In separate pot bring beans to a boil.
Add beans to ground beef along with onion, catsup and chili powder.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Good with cornbread.

title: cheese carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots; drain and add oleo.
Add eggs, milk and grated cheese.
Pour in greased 8-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, sugar and marshmallows.
Let stay in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, add other ingredients.

title: german coffee cake(naff kuchen)
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Beat well. Add eggs, beating well, about 5 minutes when mixture is light and fluffy (use electric mixer).
Add flour which has been sifted with baking powder and baking soda. Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Grease and flour a 9-inch Bundt pan, angel food pan or jello mold. Pour half the batter into pan. Now mix the 2 tablespoons of sugar, 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Also the raisins if you want.
Spread even batter in pan.
Over this pour the remaining batter.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until done.
Bake at 350°. Let cool 10 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Mix together the eggs, sugar, cinnamon, soda, flour and pumpkin and pour onto greased wax paper in a cookie sheet. Sprinkle with the nuts. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle terry cloth towel with 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Turn cake onto towel and let cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oleo; add sugar and eggs, mixing well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan or tube cake pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: happy hour mushrooms
directions: Brush mushroom caps with melted butter.
Combine softened butter, garlic and Monterey Jack cheese.
Mix well.
Add toasted onion dip mix and corn chips.
Stir in red wine and soy sauce. Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Place on baking sheet; broil until bubbly and lightly browned, about 3 minutes.

title: beef barley soup(make quick and easy)
directions: Cook barley, covered with water to 3-inches from pot top, on medium heat.
Cook about 45 minutes or until tender.
Add beef base, diced beef and frozen vegetables.
Reduce to low and cook 15 minutes more.
Serve as the main meal or a small serving to introduce your favorite entree.

title: country ham
directions: Soak ham overnight in water.
Cook in pan that seals tight or wrap in heavy-duty foil.
