Put 5 cups of water, molasses and ham together and wrap tightly in foil.
Put in cold oven; heat to 500°.
Turn off oven and let set for 3 hours.
Do not open oven. After 3 hours turn oven back on and heat to 500°.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Turn oven off and let set in oven for 12 hours or overnight.
Do not open oven until 12 hours are up.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper, celery and broccoli in butter about 10 minutes.
Cook rice according to directions.
Stir whipped cheese into rice.
Add mushroom soup to cheese and rice.
Combine to the sauteed ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° until heated and slightly brown, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil.
Brown meat; mix seasonings with tomato sauce and add 1/2 can enchilada sauce. (Pour remaining enchilada sauce over casserole.)
Pour 1/2 mix into casserole dish.
Top with 4 tortillas and 4 slices of cheese. Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Be sure to pour rest of enchilada sauce over casserole.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: lazy day fruit salad
directions: Mix together the crushed pineapple (juice and all) to the vanilla instant pudding mix and the lemon instant pudding mix. Drain the fruit cocktail and add to the mix.
Drain the mandarin oranges and add them.
Then fold in the container of Cool Whip. Spread in bowl and chill overnight.

title: cheddar baked potato slices
directions: In small bowl, combine soup, paprika and pepper.
In greased, 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange potatoes in overlapping rows. Sprinkle with cheese.
Spoon soup mixture over cheese.

title: wakey cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together in an ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
Put the shortening, vanilla, vinegar and cold water in the holes.
Mix together until smooth, then bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Break 2 eggs
into
1 cup.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and fill cup with sweet milk.
Put
into
bowl and add 1 cup sugar, 1 3/4 cups flour and 2 teaspoons baking powder.
Mix after all ingredients are together. Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350°. (Sometimes I use less sugar.)

title: country-style blueberry muffins
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the flour, oats, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in the butter or margarine until the mixture resembles coarse meal.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add last 4 ingredients to this mix.
Beat well for 2 minutes (batter will be smooth and runny).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a greased and floured cake pan.

title: easy chili
directions: Fry and brown ground round with onion (cut up).
Add tomatoes, soup, water, Chili-O mix and kidney beans.
Cook for 3/4 hour on low heat.
Stir often.

title: coffee punch
directions: Heat
and stir coffee, sugar and water until completely dissolved, let cool and add milk, vanilla and chocolate syrup. Stir well and chill. When ready to serve add ice cream.

title: tomato fettuccine with scallops
directions: Stack 8 to 10 spinach leaves, roll diagonally and cut in slivers; repeat until all are used.
Place in a large bowl.
Toss the slivered spinach leaves, tomatoes, scallions, capers, 4 tablespoons chopped dill, olive oil, salt and pepper in a large bowl; set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain.
Combine eggs, soup, cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir in broccoli.
Put mixture in a casserole dish and cover with crushed crackers.
Pour melted margarine over top of crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hen pie
directions: Season hen
with
Mrs.	Dash (to taste) before cooking. Cook hen
until	tender,
cool
and
remove
from bones.
Line baking dish
with biscuit dough (either roll thin with rolling pin or press
each
biscuit thin with fingers).
Overlap only slightly. Add boned chicken and enough broth to keep meat and bread moist. Cover
top	with biscuits done in same manner as other crust. Bake at 400° to 450° until golden brown (approximately 30 to 40 minutes).

title: pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle steak with salt and pepper.
Dip in flour.
Brown quickly in oil.
Place steak in saucepan, adding onion, water, soup and catsup.
Simmer on low heat for 45 minutes.
If steak is not tender, cook a little longer.
Add bell pepper 15 minutes before removing from heat.
Serve on hot rice.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables, celery and onions until partially tender, about 8 to 10 minutes in salt water.
Drain.
Combine cooked vegetables, mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour in a casserole dish. Combine crumbs with melted margarine. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave ham casserole
directions: Heat together soup, milk, cheddar cheese, celery salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add flaked ham and macaroni.
Pour into a 2 quart casserole.
Microwave for about 10 minutes on 70% power.

title: applesauce diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water.
Drain.
Add to raisins the applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix well.
Blend in soda and flour.
Add rest and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch greased pan, until toothpick comes out clean, about 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peaches n' cream
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine first 5 ingredients and mix until smooth.
Pour batter into a 9-inch square baking pan coated with vegetable spray.
Place peaches over batter.
In separate bowl, cream together cheese, peach juice and sugar.
Spoon mixture over peaches and spread to cover peaches completely.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Cool at least 45 minutes before serving.
Serves 12.

title: tex-mex stew
directions: Brown meat with garlic; drain.
Drain and chop tomatoes coarsely.
Save juice.
Add tomatoes, juice, picante sauce, cumin, salt and pepper to taste to the meat mixture.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Add corn, beans and onions and continue cooking uncovered for 10 minutes.
Top with cilantro (optional).
Makes 10 cups of stew.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and Karo syrup by hand.
Add pecans, vanilla and melted oleo.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: easy custard pie
directions: Thoroughly mix together the sugar, salt, eggs and vanilla. Scald the milk and slowly stir the first mixture into it.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and top with nutmeg.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425° fro 10 minutes or until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, dry onion soup mix and rice together, then roll into small to medium meatballs.
Put into a skillet and fry until medium brown.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add butter and sugar.
Beat eggs and add along with salt, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 325° for 30 minutes.
If you are using frozen shell, bake at 350° to 375°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the ground beef in the olive oil.
Add spices while browning.
Mix the spaghetti and pizza sauces together.
Add the ground beef and 1 cup of water; simmer for 1/2 hour.
Layer the sauce, noodles and cheeses in a lasagna pan and bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; add onions, pepper, garlic salt, green pepper and celery and cook about 5 minutes.
Add liquids and simmer about 2 hours.

title: cherry biscotti
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease large baking sheet. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl. Cut in butter until coarse crumbs form. Stir in nuts and cherries. Stir in eggs and vanilla. If crumbly or dry, add milk.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix everything and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven until brown or bubbling on top.

title: baked brie
directions: Bring Brie to room temperature.
Unroll crescents and pinch seams together to form two squares.
Paint bottom square with pesto. Place Brie on top.
Paint Brie with pesto and cover generously with chopped, sun-dried tomatoes.
Top with second square of crescent dough.
Pinch squares together to encase Brie.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: apple muffins
directions: Beat together real well the first 4 ingredients.
Then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in muffin cups at 400° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Fold in chopped pecans and raw apples.
Spread in well greased and lightly floured stem or flat cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions. Prepare filling by mixing spinach, egg, cheeses, salt and pepper. Layer noodles, filling and sauce twice in a baking dish. Sprinkle reserved mozzarella cheese on top. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 of the cheese.
Sprinkle this 1/2 on top of the batter.
Bake at 400° until done (about 20 to 25 minutes) in a well-greased 8-inch pan or a 12 large muffin pan.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add water and egg yolks.
Mix with rhubarb and put into unbaked pie shell.
Top with butter and bake to custard consistency.
For first 10 minutes bake pie at 425°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake until done.
Cover with meringue made from 2 egg whites and brown.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and blend until berries are thawed.
Put into this mixture the drained pineapple and pecans; pour 1/2 into a bowl and refrigerate until jellied.
Whip together cream cheese and sour cream until well blended, then spread on the top of jellied mixture.
Then make a third layer with the other 1/2 of mixture and chill again.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Layer ingredients.
Put sliced almonds and crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Shape and roll in sugar.
Flatten with fork.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 6 or 7 dozen.

title: coconut crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except berries.
Melt 1 stick butter in 9 x 13 pan. Pour mixture over melted butter. Add 1 cup of berries (any kind). Bake at 350° until browned.

title: emerald chiffon
directions: Add hot water to jello; stir until it is dissolved. Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Mix 1/4 cup water and Kool-Aid to make juice; mix with beaten egg yolks and sugar.
Cook until it thickens; let cool.
Whip cream.
Beat egg whites.
Fold jello and egg yolk mixture into cream, then fold into egg whites. Pour over half the cookie crumbs which have been arranged in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put remaining crumbs over top and chill about 2 hours or until ready to serve.

title: baked chicken
directions: In a 9 x
12-inch greased pan, put uncooked rice.
Pour over rice 2 cups
hot water, then put on chicken pieces.
Salt and pepper to taste,
then
sprinkle
1 package dry onion soup mix. Cover tightly with
foil
and
bake
at
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: moonshine gingerbread
directions: Blend together the flour, sugar and butter to form a crumbly mixture.
Reserve 1 cup.
To the remaining mixture, add ginger, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Add egg and then soda mixed with sour milk.
Beat thoroughly.
Put half of reserved crumbly mixture on the bottom of 8 or 9-inch square baking pan. Pour batter on top and sprinkle with remaining crumbly mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken upside-down
directions: Melt butter over low heat. Add flour, salt and pepper. Let come to a boil over low heat. Remove from heat. Add chicken broth and milk. Return to heat; bring to a boil, stirring all the time. Boil 1 minute. Cut heat to low and fold in chicken, peas and lemon juice. Top with Cornbread Topping and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and milk together and bring to a boil. Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of lukewarm water. When yeast is dissolved, stir into lukewarm milk mixture.

title: ricotta pie
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and Ricotta.
Add beaten eggs and fold into mixture.
Add vanilla and milk.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell (unbaked).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce in small pieces and place in a large bowl. Liberally sprinkle on celery seed to taste.
Place eggs on top of this, then peas, then onions, then bacon.
Mix sugar with Miracle Whip; spread onto salad.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Chill.

title: layered turkey and dressing
directions: In a casserole dish, lay turkey only to cover bottom.
Add a layer of dressing.
Add another layer of turkey.
Continue in this fashion until all turkey and dressing is gone.
Pour gravy over casserole.
Put in oven at 350° to heat the turkey.
Do not overcook.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; set aside. Grease 4 (8-inch) round cake pans; set aside. After Parkerhouse Rolls dough has risen per directions; sift 1/2 cup flour in a thick layer evenly over work surface. Turn half of dough out onto floured surface. (Dough will be very soft.) Set remaining half of dough aside. Sift 1/4 cup flour evenly over dough. Roll dough into a 30 x 20-inch rectangle. Spread half of cinnamon mixture over dough. Roll up dough jellyroll fashion, starting at the short side, just to the center of the rectangle; cut dough alongside of roll to release it. Roll up remaining half of rectangle in the same fashion. Set rolls of dough aside. Repeat procedure using remaining 3/4 cup flour, dough and cinnamon mixture. Cut each roll of dough into 16 (1 1/4-inch thick) slices. Place 16 slices, cut sides down, in each prepared pan, leaving 1/4-inch space between slices. Brush slices with 1/2 cup melted butter. Let rise, uncovered, in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: peanut butter fruit sauce
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Simmer 10 minutes. Cool.
In a large bowl, stir mixture into peanut butter and raisins.
Spoon over fresh fruit cup.
Yields 1 1/3 cups.

title: white chili
directions: In skillet, with a little oil, saute chicken breasts, cut in small pieces and set aside.
In large soup pot, in 1 tablespoon oil, saute onions.
Add remaining ingredients to sauteed onions except for the yogurt or sour cream, salsa and cheese.
Stir, cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Serve in bowls and top with 1 1/2 tablespoons yogurt or sour cream and 1 1/2 tablespoons salsa. Sprinkle on grated cheese.
Good and different soup!

title: cherry bing bars
directions: Bring to a rapid boil the sugar, evaporated milk, margarine and salt for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.

title: lenten tuna fish casserole
directions: Put ingredients in casserole in the following order: layer of noodles, layer of cream sauce in which processed cheese has been melted, layer of mushrooms, layer of tuna, layer of asparagus, then repeat.
Dot top with grated cheese and bread crumbs. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: dill carrots
directions: Boil carrots until just tender.
Make mixture of vinegar, salt, sugar, and dill weed and soak carrots for several hours or overnight.	Drop carrots into this mixture while still hot. Before serving, remove carrots, reserving liquid.
Serve on a dish with a sprinkling of the parsley.
Also the reserved liquid may be used again.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Mix soda with 1/2 cup water. Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour 4 (9-inch) cake pans.
Pour batter into pans and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Fill burrito shells with mixture of sour cream, onion, soup and chicken meat.
Sprinkle with cheese and roll up.
Sprinkle cheese over top, if desired.
Heat in microwave.
Serve with salsa.

title: pineapple dish
directions: Drain pineapple and mix pineapple, eggs, flour and sugar together.
Melt butter and mix butter and toast, cut into 1/2 x 1/2-inch squares.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a covered casserole dish.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Mix lightly.
Pour into 1-quart casserole; sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 375° in greased pan until center is firm.

title: crispy chocolate bars
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Add 1 cup sugar and 1 cup chopped dates and boil again.
Stir.
Add 1 well beaten egg, then add 2 1/2 cups Rice Krispies, 1
cup nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool and make into balls and roll in coconut or 10x sugar.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine all and cook for at least 2 1/2 hours.

title: peach dumpling
directions: Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine flour, sugar, milk and baking powder and pour over melted butter.
Pour peaches over this.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Wrap tortillas in aluminum foil; place on an ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until heated. Brown sausage in a skillet, stirring until it crumbles; drain and set aside.
Add potatoes, green pepper and onion to skillet; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Add eggs, butter, salt and pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until eggs are firm, but still moist.
Remove from heat; stir in reserved sausage.
Work with 1 tortilla at a time, keeping remaining tortillas covered and warm.
Place about 3/4 cup egg mixture onto each tortilla.
Roll up tightly and place, seam side down, in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with taco sauce.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: bacon cheese braid
directions: Scald milk, then add sugar, salt, margarine and beaten eggs; cool it. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water. Then add to milk. Add 4 cups flour. Stir well and add rest of flour. Knead on floured board 10 to 15 minutes. Place in greased bowl and turn to coat. Cover and let rise until double (1 to 1 1/2 hours). Punch down and let rise again (30 to 45 minutes). Shape half dough as desired, loaf or rolls.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Clean chicken and place in bottom of crock-pot.
Put tomato and mushroom soup on top of the chicken.
Do not stir.
Add onion on top of soup.
Turn crock-pot on low-medium for 8 to 10 hours. Serve over noodles or with mashed potatoes.

title: frozen strawberry-yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into cool whip, blending well.
Fold in strawberries.
Spoon into crust and freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer about 30 minutes before serving.

title: glazed nuts
directions: Add water to egg white; stir in sugar, salt and spices.
Mix well.
Add nuts and stir until coated.
Place nuts, flat side down, on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: sallye's hot spiced fruit
directions: Drain fruit, reserving 1/2 cup liquid from each fruit. Combine syrups, marmalade, margarine and spices in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes. Reduce heat, stir in fruit and simmer 20 minutes. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: mincemeat icebox cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars together until very creamy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to butter mixture, alternating with mincemeat.
Fold in nuts.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch size rolls and refrigerate overnight.
When ready, slice about 1/4 inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 or 5 dozen.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring the hot water, chicken, salt, celery, onion and carrot to a boil.
Remove foam.
Cover.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Beat 4 eggs. Mix with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Add to boiling broth, stirring continuously until eggs are set.
Remove from heat.

title: vegetable and sausage soup
directions: Boil salt pork in a pot of water.
Simmer pork 1 hour and transfer pork to a dish with a slotted spoon.
In another pan, boil Great Northern beans in 2 cups water for 2 minutes.
Remove pan from the heat and soak beans 1 hour.
Drain beans and put into a pot with 9 cups of hot water and cook 45 minutes.
Add carrot, turnip, leek, celery, onion and a cheesecloth bag containing parsley, thyme, bay leaf and salt and the salt pork.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to moderately low and simmer 45 minutes.
Add kielbasa sausage.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices and add 1/4 pound beans (green), trimmed and cut into 1-inch pieces and simmer soup for 30 minutes.
Remove and discard the celery and cheesecloth bag and adjust seasoning.
Serve with crusty French bread.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and set aside.
Place rice in bottom of oblong baking dish.
Mix soups and water.
Pour over rice.
Lay chicken pieces on top and bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: crab imperial
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs and cheese in a bowl.
Mix well, then let sit for 1 hour. Place in the buttered casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and Parmesan cheese and dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage, onion, green pepper and celery.
Put soup, water and rice in baking dish.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, water and cocoa.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Pour on a large greased cookie sheet with sides. Bake at 375° for 20 to 22 minutes. Ice immediately with the following.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown and drain hamburger with onion; add other ingredients except cheese and tortillas.
Simmer until well mixed.
Quarter tortillas.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer meat mixture, cheese and tortillas (2 to 3 layers), ending with cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with chips and hot sauce.

title: cilantro dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Makes 1/2 cup dressing.

title: christmas rock cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and blend well.
Add soda which has been dissolved in water.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet. Bake about 5 to 8 minutes in 350° oven.
Use half red and half green candied cherries for more color.
You can use half black and half English walnuts if you like.

title: baked turkey
directions: Put water in broiler pan. Place turkey on rack and cover tightly with foil. Cook 1 1/2 hours at 500°. Let set overnight.

title: hot or cold chicken salad
directions: Combine the chicken, onion, celery and green pepper.
Mix the cream, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and vinegar for dressing.
Add the cashews.
Combine chicken mixture and dressing.
Heat in oven, if desired to serve hot, at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Pour potatoes and beef into baking dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Spoon sour cream over mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted.
Serve with salad.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line an 8 or 9-inch pie pan with the crescent roll dough. Brown the loose sausage meat and place over dough.
Beat the eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over the sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: melon slush
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil; let cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in freezer.
When ready to use, place 2 tablespoons mixture in glass and add ginger ale.
Very refreshing.

title: the ultimate bubble recipe
directions: Mix ingredients in a shallow pan.
(The glycerine makes bubbles stronger and they last longer.)

title: eclair cake
directions: Grease a sheet cake pan with butter.
Put one layer of crackers to cover bottom.
Layer large pudding (use half of pudding), one layer of crackers, one layer of Cool Whip, one layer of crackers, one layer of pudding (the other half) and one layer of crackers.

title: crawfish bread
directions: Slice French bread in half.
In pan, melt margarine, add onion, bell pepper, garlic, saute a few minutes, then add crawfish, parsley and seasoned salt.
Saute for about 10 minutes. Add cheese, stir until cheese is melted.
Spread on French bread. Bake in 400° oven for about 15 minutes.
Cut into pieces and enjoy.
Shrimp may be substituted for crawfish.

title: honey and poppy seed biscuits
directions: In a blender, combine cottage cheese, milk and honey.
Cover and blend until nearly smooth.
Prepare biscuit mix according to package, except substitute pureed mixture and poppy seed for the liquid.
Bake as directed on the package directions.
Makes 12 to 14 biscuits.

title: butter cookie sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and sugar until creamy. Add egg and vanilla and beat.
Stir in flour.
Roll into rounds and bake.
When cool, put together with jelly.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: japanese fruitcake
directions: Mix together the butter or margarine, sugar, eggs, cake flour, baking powder, milk and vanilla flavoring.
Put 1/2 of batter into 2 round baking pans.
Add cinnamon, ground cloves, nutmeg and raisins.
This will make 2 spice layers.
Bake all layers at 350° for 30 minutes or until top springs back.
Let cool completely.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Place thawed hash brown potatoes in casserole.
Mix chicken soup, sour cream, onion, cheese, salt and pepper together and pour this mixture over potatoes.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: banana pudding
directions: Whip instant pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip and then sour cream and vanilla extract, mix until stiff.
Line dish with a layer of vanilla wafers, then a layer of bananas and then a layer of pudding until the dish is full.
Serves 8.

title: golden fruit salad
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch, reserved pineapple juice, lemon juice and orange juice.
Stir and boil 1 minute.
Pour hot mixture over fruit.
Leave uncovered until cool.

title: banana applesauce muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash bananas, cream butter and sugar. Add remaining ingredients.
Fill muffin cups halfway and bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Use toothpick to test for doneness.
Yields 16 large muffins.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast on 1/2 cup warm water; stir to dissolve.
Melt shortening.
Remove from heat.
Add honey and remaining 4 1/2 cups water.
Mix whole wheat flour, instant potatoes, dry milk and salt.
Add to saucepan and beat until smooth.
Add yeast and beat to blend.
Then with wooden spoon, mix in enough all-purpose flour, a little at a time, to make a dough that leaves the sides of the pan.

title: baked tuna noodle casserole
directions: In small saucepan, cook soup mix in water.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Then in a medium saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Gradually stir in hot soup and cook until thickened.
Add tuna and fold in peas and onions.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: orange slush punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in a Dutch oven; cook over high heat, stirring often, until sugar dissolves.
Let mixture cool.
Add bananas and next 3 ingredients to sugar mixture; stir well. Freeze until firm.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and garlic.
In large pan, combine all ingredients.
Cook 2 1/2 hours on low heat.
You may take another pound of hamburger and make meatballs.
To this add 1 egg, 1/4 cup chopped onion and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Shape into balls and brown.
Add to sauce and cook with other ingredients.

title: peach & lemon graham cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° F.
Spray 8-inch round, deep, fluted, nonstick cake pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Place butter in mixing bowl, and sugar and beat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in lemon peel, lemon zest and peach.
Slowly add milk, extracts and lemon juice.
Place crumbs in separate bowl and stir in salt, baking powder, baking soda and cake flour.
Fold egg mixture into crumbs until well combined. Pour batter into cake pan, smoothing top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until center of cake is firm.
Remove from oven and cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pan and cool on cake rack.

title: buttermilk crumb cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together until crumbly.
Take 3/4 cup out and add cinnamon; this will be the topping.
Then add soda, baking powder, egg and buttermilk to remaining mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan 25 minutes at 350°.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan.
Add sugar and syrup.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly; simmer for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla; blend well.
Pour over popcorn, nuts, gumdrops and marshmallows. Let stand 2 minutes, then shape into tube pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan; add crumbs and seasonings.
Mix together until well blended.
Moisten with water and stuff chops. Brown chops in skillet first, then bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn once or twice during baking.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly and place in baking dish.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Mix together and freeze in a 9-inch graham cracker (or vanilla wafer) crust.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed.
Bake in a well-greased pan at 450° until nicely browned.
Serves 12 people.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Pan-fry pork chops in oil until brown.
Add onion and green pepper.
Mix chicken broth, water, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over pork chops. Add rice.
Cover and simmer over low heat for about 45 minutes or until rice is cooked and most liquid is absorbed.

title: butter nutty cake
directions: Mix 1 egg, cake mix, melted margarine and nuts with fingers. Pat into greased and floured oblong pan, 9 x 13.

title: summer squash
directions: Boil squash until tender (in water or red wine).
Place in baking dish with tomatoes and chiles; top with cheese.
Bake until warmed through and cheese is melted.

title: golden carrots and onions
directions: Cook carrots in 1 cup water with bouillon cubes. Saute onions in butter until golden (keep lid on). Mix flour in 1/2 cup cold water and add to onion. Heat until thickened.
Add carrots in broth and 1/4 teaspoon pepper to onions.
Mix. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: tropical yogurt shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Mix on high speed for 30 seconds until blended.
Serve immediately.

title: 1 chicken taco
directions: Remove skin from chicken and simmer until meat falls off the bone.
Cut meat into small pieces in a skillet.
Combine cooked chicken, taco mix and 1 1/2 cups water.
Bring to a boil, the simmer to desired consistency (10 to 15 minutes).
Heat tortillas, then fix.

title: corn pudding bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sherried scallops and mushrooms
directions: Combine butter and seasonings in a 2-quart glass dish. Microwave on High (max power) for 3 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Flour and grease loaf pans.
Put everything in one big bowl together.
Mix well.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake about 1 hour.
Makes about 5 large loaves.

title: father's favorite meat loaf
directions: For meat loaf, two pounds of ground round then add a pound of chuck steak ground.
A cup of taters, then you mash and beat two eggs into the hash.
One large onion, all chopped up, some fresh sweet milk, about a cup.
Half a cup catsup, this will do, one cup applesauce, add it too, two teaspoons use to salt it down and one of sugar, beat be brown.
One tablespoon green pepper flakes, one parsley, celery, too it takes.
Half teaspoon each of nutmeg, cloves; half teaspoon allspice, also goes.
One teaspoon Accent, pepper to taste, then stir til mixture is a paste.
Now form in loaf, and let it bake.
Which sixty minutes more will take.
(Bake in 350° oven°.)

title: berry (apple) bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Grease a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Line with wax paper, grease again.

title: red snapper royale
directions: In shallow pan over medium heat, poach fish fillets in wine to cover with lemon and 2 tsp basil.
Remove fish from pan and break into large chunks, being careful to remove all bones.
Set aside.
Microwave spinach 6 minutes on high.
Squeeze all water out and set aside.
Saute shallots and 2 tsp fresh basil in butter over medium heat until tender, 5 minutes.
Add flour and cook, stirring constantly, until light sand-colored.
Blend in half & half and whisk in tomato paste and 2 tsp basil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spread spinach over bottom of large, greased baking dish, then layer fish pieces on spinach.
Pour sauce over all and top with cheese.
Bake until bubbly, 20 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain can fruit cocktail into small bowl.

title: candy cane bread
directions: Stir together flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add nuts.
Mix egg and milk.
Stir into dry mixture just until moistened.
On a lightly floured surface, pat dough to a 10 x 7-inch rectangle, 1/2-inch thick.
Cut crosswise into 1-inch strips.
Twist each strip by holding both ends.
Bend one end to form a candy cane.
Place several inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until light brown. Carefully transfer to rack.
Cool.
Coat each cane with Powdered Sugar Icing.
Decorate using decorator icing, cinnamon candies or peppermint candies as desired.
Makes 10.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; press into pie pan.
Bake until golden brown.
Set aside and cool.

title: sour cream cake(by ilene a. nichols)
directions: Take 3/4 cup of the sugar and mix with the walnuts and cinnamon topping.
Cream butter and add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and vanilla.
Take 1/2 of flour, baking soda, baking powder and a dash of salt.
Mix with 1/2 of sour cream, butter, eggs and sugar.
Add rest of flour and sour cream.

title: polish kraut bake
directions: Heat oil in skillet and fry onions on medium heat until caramelized.
Set aside.
Brown sausage.
Layer half of the sauerkraut in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Then layer half the onions.
Next, layer all of the sausage, the other half of the sauerkraut and onions.
Mix the water and soup together and pour over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil the last 15 minutes.
Better made early and reheated.

title: baked bananas
directions: In a small saucepan, combine juice, wine, honey, orange rind, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Heat until warm.
Peel bananas and split them in half lengthwise.
Place bananas, cut side down, in a greased baking dish large enough to accommodate the bananas without crowding them.
Pour sauce over bananas.
Sprinkle with almonds and dot with margarine, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for a total of 25 minutes, basting bananas with sauce after the first 15 minutes of baking.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix together.
Use as a dip with crackers.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Cook tomatoes; season with salt, black pepper, sugar and onion.
Add bread and butter.
Stew in saucepan until all is tender and thickened.
Serve.

title: mango bread
directions: To mango mixture, add sugar, eggs, coconut and oil; beat to blend.
Stir flour with baking powder and add to mango mixture. Beat until the batter is very well blended.
Pour into an oiled 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven until loaf is richly browned and has pulled slightly from pan sides and top springs back when firmly pressed, 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes, then invert bread onto a rack.
Serve warm or cool.
If making ahead, let cool; wrap airtight and store at room temperature up to a day.
Freeze to store longer.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: blueberry pie deluxe
directions: Boil 1 cup blueberries with 1 cup water and sugar; strain, reserving liquid.
Add cornstarch to reserved liquid; oil in sauce pan, stirring until thickened.
Place remaining blueberries in large bowl; add lemon juice.
Pour boiling mixture over blueberries; cool.
Place whipped cream in baked pie shell, spoon in blueberry mixture.
Chill for several hours.

title: new yorker cheese cake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan; then dust with crumbs, rolling to coat.
Place pan in oven for about 4 minutes.
Remove to rack and keep oven at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Whip cream, make Jello with 1 cup hot water

and 1 cup cold water and let Jello slightly thicken. Let cream cheese get real soft. Mix sugar with it, fold in whipped cream and Jello into the cream cheese. Add vanilla. Put into a graham cracker crust. Put in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.

title: amy's chili
directions: First, brown the meat in a saucepan and drain off the fat. Put the rest of the ingredients except chili powder and cumin into a pot with a lid and set it on medium-low to simmer for about 10 minutes.
Then, add 3 to 4 teaspoons of chili powder and ground cumin, more or less, if desired.
Cook this down for about 10 more minutes on low with the lid on.
(It's usually better on the second day.)
Serve it alone or with Cheddar cheese or sour cream on top.

title: korean roast chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Turn and bake an additional 15 minutes or until done.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt the ingredients in a double boiler and dip balls in it.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Cream margarine and shortening together.
Add eggs, one at a time, to creamed mixture, blending well each time.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternating with milk and vanilla mixture.
Cook in greased and lightly floured tube or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop from tip of spoon. Bake in a 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Store in airtight container.

title: diabetic no-bake cookies
directions: Combine skim milk, cocoa powder and margarine in pan.
Heat until boils, stirring constantly.
Remove pan from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats, vanilla and Equal.
Cool, then drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Makes 50 cookies.
Two cookies equals 1 cal. pt., 1/2 bread and 1 fat exchange and 2 1/2 na pts.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour and other ingredients. Spray tube pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry delight cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into three greased 8 inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 27 to 29 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: doggie treats
directions: Form into ball and knead about 1/2 minute.
Roll out dough 3/8 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters or just into shapes.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, until slightly brown and firm.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer half each of meat mixture, chops and cheese in 2-quart casserole dish. Repeat layer.
Bake 20 minutes. Top with shredded lettuce and tomatoes.

title: seafoam
directions: Combine sugars and water in saucepan.
Stir until well dissolved.
Add syrup and cook to 252° for hard ball stage.
Pour slowly over well beaten egg whites.
Beat until mixture is light and fluffy and piles up without spreading.
Add vanilla and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes 3 dozen pieces.

title: tomato-broccoli quiche
directions: Line 11 x 7-inch baking dish with pie crust.
Cook broccoli and onion, covered, with butter and water about 5 minutes, just until tender.
Remove from heat.
Beat cream and eggs together; add Swiss cheese, salt, pepper, nutmeg and broccoli mixture.
Combine Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese mixture on bottom of crust.
Dip tomato slices in mixture and arrange in layer on crust.
Pour in broccoli mixture.
Dip remaining tomato slices in Parmesan cheese mixture and arrange on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cool 20 minutes before cutting.

title: texas calico beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper towel and drain.
Cook beef in small amount bacon fat.
Add onions and cook until tender. Combine beef, onions, ketchup, salt, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar in 3-quart casserole.
Drain cans of beans (save some liquid in case mixture is dry).
Mix thoroughly with beef mixture. Sprinkle with bacon which has been crumbled.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
May add onion and celery soup to ingredients, if desired.

title: microwave chicken breast diane
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of wax paper.
Pound slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: flounder poached in fresh tomato sauce
directions: Cook the onion and garlic in the olive oil until soft.
Add the wine, basil and marjoram.
Simmer until most of the liquid evaporates.
Add the tomatoes and simmer 3 minutes.
Place the flounder fillets in the simmering sauce, cover and cook gently for 2 minutes, just until fish is firm.
Remove fish, add the lemon juice to the sauce, salt and pepper to taste, and pour over the fish.

title: egg bake
directions: Place bread in a glass 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine rest of ingredients and pour on top. Bake 1 hour at 325° uncovered. Bake 1 hour at 350° to 375° if using a metal pan.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Using juices created during preparation, mix with a bit of the liqueur and pour over the salad.
This will keep the salad fresh for a couple of days.

title: soup by ellie
directions: If sausage is hot, no spices need to be added.
Otherwise improve!
Brown sausage.
Add rest of ingredients, except for the cabbage. Add cabbage approximately 20 minutes before serving the soup.
